ra Sheldon about this request.  Discussed the proposed workflow for this request.  Barbara Sheldon is requesting updated screen shots of proposed smart group to discuss with the Respiratory Therapy Leads meeting October 9th.  She understands that my recommendation is to embed a smart group within specialty/ selected order sets vs. her original request for a stand alone order set (for 2 orders).  After agreement from Barbara S. after her October 9th meeting, it will be necessary to vet this request among HBS, ICU, and ED domain groups.  Then I will need to request a new EAP record that says \"Request RT to perform Sputum Induction\" this will route to the \"respiratory section\" of the PER (after consultation with Stephanie Gavigan we are unable to route it to the nursing comm section) with a frequency of per comments so Nursing may release this order if they are unable to obtain a sputum specimen and it will route to the RT inbasket pool.  The orders for hypertonic saline cannot be pre selected because a clinical decision needs to be made if the patient has Pneumocystis (for 3% solution), the details of the hypertonic saline orders should be as needed one time for sputum induction.<BR><BR>2009-09-15 - Sherry Ellis - Sent new screen shots today.<BR><BR>2009-11-05 - Sherry Ellis - Sent email to Barbara Sheldon and Janet Margolis inquiring to the status of this request following their Oct 9th regional RT meeting.<BR><BR>2009-12-02 - Sherry Ellis - Recieved email from Janet Margolis and Barbara Sheldon on 11/24/09 with further enhancements to SR per Dr. Maurice Franco.  Replied to email today advising them that the number of sputum collections is done at the order level as well as the hour frequency that they would like (see attachement dated today).  If additional respiratory micro labs are desired, Janet (or site support) to update this SR with requested labs.  THH will then forward request to domain leads (HBS, ED , ICU) and direct questions to Janet and Dr. Franco.<