IDE OF THIS ORDERSET (e.g. as part of medication reconciliation or continuation of prior prescription)\n\n\nWe should probably hold off from sending this out for review until we know more about the status of the BPA and whether the orders can come across into the discharge instructions.  This orderset is not being used frequently and this may not be the solution if are not able to have a BPA fire.\n\nName of Order Set:	\nHBS ACS and HBS CHF\n\nPurpose/intent of order set (and does this replace any existing order sets):\nThe ACE/ARB sections of the ACS and CHF ordersets and the statin section of the ACS orderset are being revised to facilitate accurate documentation, data capture, decision support tools, and more rapid data review for improved core measure adherence, \n\nBackground information/context setting:\n\nJoint Commission Core Measures are publicly reported data of our organizations adherence to evidence based guidelines.  Significant resources are applied both locally and regionally to meet these goals.  These changes are designed to facilitate adherence to these practice guidelines or document contraindications as indicated.  Mor',NULL,'1191454019?X441117?Jeremy D Vang\n\nPer Brain Hoberman.  Refer to Tina.  Tina to refer to Alan Whippy and the core measure experts.?1195538255?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\n10/9/07 Request forwarded to Ann Chang for review by core measures group?1196140098?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nFollow up note to Ann Chang inquiring as to status.?1196450375?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\n11/27 Anne Chang forwarded request to Dr. Phil Lee. Dr. Lee is reviewing the CAR forms for core measures revisions.?1203307418?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nInfo sent to Dr. Lee to confirm add in upcoming revision?1211997497?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nPer Anne Chang email 1/22/08\n\nAspirin Orders – Please Select ONE From The Following Choices:\n0 Enteric Coated Aspirin 325 MG ORAL DAILY. First dose now if not given in the ED.\n0 Enteric Coated Aspirin 162 MG ORAL DAILY. First dose now if not given in the ED.\nCONTRAINDICATION TO ASPIRIN ON ADMISSION DUE TO: (select all that apply)\nallergy\nrecent coumadin/warfarin\nbleed\nother reason____\n\nBeta Blockers -- Please select AT LEAST ONE from the following choices:\n(Hold for Heart Rate less than 60 or Systolic Blood Pressure less than 90.)\n0 Metoprolol (LOPRESSOR) 5 MG IV every 5 minutes for 3 doses\n0 Metoprolol (LOPRESSOR) 25 MG ORAL 2 TIMES A DAY\n0 Atenolol (TENORMIN) 25 MG ORAL DAILY\nCONTRAINDICATION TO BETA BLOCKERS ON ADMISSIONDUE TO: (select all that apply)\nallergy\nbradycardia\nsecond or third degree heart block on ECG (with no pacemaker)\nheart failure \nshock on arrival or w/in 24 hrs of arrival\nother reason_____\n\nOther Medications\n0 Lisinopril (ZESTRIL/PRINIVIL) 10 MG ORAL DAILY.  Hold for Heart Rate less than 60 or Systolic Blood Pressure less than 90. \nCONTRAINDICATION TO ACEI DUE TO: (select all that apply)\nallergy\nmoderate/severe aortic stenosis\nangioedema \nhyperkalemia\nrenal artery stenosis\nworsening renal function/renal disease/dysfuntion\nother reason______\n0 Losartan (COZAAR) 25 MG ORAL DAILY.  Hold for Heart Rate less than 60 or Systolic Blood Pressure less than 90',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2168,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Elliot Morrison','Jaya Mokkapati, Regional PCS',3001879,NULL,'Create Triage Standing order set',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,NULL,'L','N','H','0','OB Standing Triage',NULL,'','test released in stgn','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ','0','NR','N','N','PERN','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-17 13:29:16','2009-02-24 13:30:16','2009-02-25 09:45:14','2009-02-25 13:43:36','2008-10-09 16:51:46',' ','','','','',NULL,'','','',968,NULL,201,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-14 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-0