ith in my smartphrase.  I will also sit down with Kelly and have him develop his own smartphrase for the short term fix.  In addition, I will be contacting the local \"RIMS\" group to see if they can rectify this problem quicker.  \n\nMy plan for the format is to have an initial bioethics form created under the \"initial assessment\" form of a patients chart.  This way, we can get a format that automatically populates the assessment form with needed information (i.e. demographics) that are already in the chart.  I hope this helps, I will meet with Kelly next week.  \n\nJennifer M. Baur, LCSW\n\nNOTICE TO RECIPIENT:  If you are not the intended recipient of this e-mail, you are prohibited from sharing, copying, or otherwise using or disclosing its contents.  If you have received this e-mail in error, please notify the sender immediately by reply e-mail and permanently delete this e-mail and any attachments without reading, forwarding or saving them.  Thank you.\n\n\n<BR><BR>2007-10-25 - Elizabeth D Will - Elizabeth D Will\n\nHi,\n\nFYI: The original email in this thread discusses this being located in a patients chart, re: Demographics information there. \n\nThat is an IP2 ClinDoc request.  If that is the case, we would not be creating a new form in the ADT workflow navigator.  Only question for us would be whether ClinDoc felt it pertinent to have the info mapped back to ADT.\n\nFrom this description, I dont think this is ADT.\n::::::::::::::::::original email request::::::::::::::::::\nI have worked the last two days on this form.  I have created my own smartphrase to start this process.  I have spoken with Jean Lai Lee with the Health Connect building team.  She recommended you send her an email with the following information to make this request a high priority.  She stated we needed to site JCAHO compliance issues and/or specific legislation/ Kaiser policy that would bump this form up in priority.  The ADT group meets on February 14 and will be discussing the pr