ent to requestor today.?1194035710?M491788?Britt L Mattern\n\nLisa, per Brian, this is not interpretable.  If we cant get more info, lets close this.?1194338146?S342302?Lisa M Rohr\n\nClarification :\nOften in the ICU, patients have an IV of Normal Saline or LR running at low rate .  If a fluid bolus is needed, it is administered from this existing bag of fluids.  However, in KPHC, when the order for an IV bolus is entered, it registers on the MAR (and then on the flowsheet) as a *new* IV Fluid.  The result is that there are multiples lines on the Doc Flowsheet for NS or LR (even though only one bag of fluid is hanging).\n\nSo, this request is to have LR and NS behave the same way as titratable medications, therefore, adjustments can be made to the rate without complicating the flowsheet.\n\nI will attach a screenshot to illustrate this issue.?1214434825?D899443?Alexander H Koppel\n\nChris to f/u with Brian and close if he denies this.?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2184,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1967002,NULL,'SSC-IP2:  Perinatal is requesting a system report or list that will contain both scheduled inductions and c-sections.',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','0','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'0','Clo','0','KPHC CN RIMS','RIMS','End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Enhancement','','L','N','Y','S','0','NR',' ','N','PERN','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-04 15:35:10','2008-12-05 12:19:26','2007-09-20 10:49:33',' ','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,1124,NULL,197,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL