 \"Contraindication\" orders.  To give some history and background on this section of the order set, Cathy Norbutas and I came up with this as a way to prompt the MD to document aspirin status on chest pain patients, even if it was just in the orders.  What happens now is that the two first options- NOT GIVEN, ALREADY GIVEN PRIOR TO ED ARRIVAL and NOT GIVEN, SUSPECTED NON-CARDIAC CHEST PAIN-- trigger a contraindication flag which must then be acknowledged before moving on.  This ends up being a bit of an annoyance.\n\n     However, it is not the biggest issue with this section.  When opening this orderset, one is forced to choose one of the options.  This is true if youve already opened and used the order set.  I had a case where I wanted to order NTG drip on a patient whose Troponin came back positive after he had been here awhile (we still suffer here at SSC without bedside Troponins). The order set is the quickest place to find this, which I knew (and the order in the Preference List is worded differently, and I think incorrectly).  However, you cannot sign the order for the NTG drip without first either ordering something from the Anti Platelet section, forcing you to either a) order aspirin, which is already on board, or b) fire off a contraindication alert, which is not what I want either.\n\nIdeally these options within the Anti-Platelet section would be changed to what the original intent was, which is a way to simply document the aspirin status, or order aspirin if need be.  Im not sure if putting Communication orders within this section is possible or impossible w/in EPIC- I know that there are some limitations on what can be grouped together.',NULL,'1196189955ï££H521379ï££Tina H Hamilton\n\nTIGR review; options explored. Referred to Core Measures and ED domain leads for review.ï£¢1201141773ï££M491788ï££Britt L Mattern\n\nSpoke with Brian.  Solution is likely to request new EAP records.  Sherry and Alex to work out the request.  Look at all ordersets that have contraindications to find all the problem areas.  As for the second part of the SR (re-opening an orderset and being required to select an order from a required section is annoying because they already placed that order the first time they opened the orderset) is something for which we have no technical solution.ï£¢1207016548ï££H521379ï££Tina H Hamilton\n\nNote to S Ellis and A Koppel inquiring as to status of analysis and new EAP recordsï£¢',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2192,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2022405,NULL,'OS NEW CARD Interfacility Cardiac Transport Orders :  AP Baseline RN is requesting an order set change for',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','0','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'0','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','Y',' ','0','NR',' ','N','MEDSURG','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 18:59:21','2009-02-24 19:00:21','2009-02-25 09:50:23','2009-02-25 13:43:57','2007-10-11 13:25:10',' ','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,965,NULL,197,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-11-14 03:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OS NEW CARD Interfacility Cardiac Transport Orders : AP Baseline RN is requesting an order set change for SSC Cardi