-----\n- Recently there have been cases where two supplements or two tube feeding formulas have been ordered at once.  Note that more than one supplement or TF can exist at one time (there are some locations that want this flexibility).  If you wish to replace one TF formula or supplement with another, the first order must be discontinued.  In the case of supplements and TF, the ORDERS MODIFY option creates a new order with changes, however, doesnt discontinue the previous order as it does with diet orders.  With diets,  only one can exist at a time...so when a diet is modified the previous diet discontinues.  However, since more than one supplement or TF can be ordered at once, modifying the order creates a new order and also keeps the old order.  IT IS FINE TO USE ORDERS MODIFY TO MODIFY A SUPPLEMENT OR TF ORDER IF IT IS EASIER THAN CREATING A NEW ORDER, HOWEVER, THE ORIGINAL ORDER MUST THEN BE DISCONTINUED.  AGAIN, THIS APPLIES TO SUPPLEMENTS AND FORMULAS AND NOT TO DIET ORDERS.\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n- I know we discussed the Duplicate Orders Notification Alert for KP Health Connect orders in the past and Nor CA was going to use the BAP instead.  I am going to ask again  for the Duplicate Orders Notification Alert to be turned on in Nor CA.\n\nAs you can see from Mary Harts e-mail below, we continue to have problems with users discontinuing previous supplements.  \n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n- I agree ....please open a remedy ticket for a Duplicate Orders Notification Alert.\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n- this request was submitted by Jennifer Baker,',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-30 - Denise M Seymour - Nurse Facility Lead SR Review Mtg 10/30: Reassigning to SSC per Marleen Mann for further clarification. Need to know what exactly is needed.<BR><BR>2008-10-30 - Michael A Youssef - Cheryl to f