 desired benefit. Therefore, the Amiodarone HBS Order Set is now being revised to include decision support language describing amiodarones unique properties and how best ordering practices should reflect these characteristics. Non-standard dosing options for amiodarone have been removed. Rather, standard oral loading and tapering regimens have been included (these orders for tapering doses can be edited and tailored to individual patient needs, as appropriate). With these loading regimens, it is important to follow serial EKGs for QT prolongation and for nurses to contact a physician when a patients rhythm changes or converts to normal sinus rhythm; these orders have been added as well.\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nPhilip C Lee, MD, Inpatient Cardiology Domain Lead\nMichael Lauer, MD, KPNC Electrophysiologist\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\nCardiology and Electrophysiology',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2200,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Maggie Mentakis','',3104022,NULL,'Add VTE prophylaxis section to thoracic postop order set (414249)',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'L','R','M','D','',NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NOWRK','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','M','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','PERI','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-26 10:25:02','2008-11-26 17:52:02','2008-12-01 11:02:48','2008-11-12 15:36:55',' ',NULL,'','','',NULL,'','','',459,NULL,201,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-18 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL