ives from the 3 KPNC main cardiology facilities (WCR, SFO, SCH) which provide tertiary care for the most complex cardiology patients.  Input was received from this summit and reviewed for appropriateness and consensus.  This order set was built with the following considerations in mind:\n--requests were received for order sets related to pre- and post-pacemaker implantation, pre- and post-defibrillator implantation, pre- and post-electrophysiology study, and cardioversion\n--it was decided that all of these order sets could be consolidated into TWO order sets entitled: Pre-Device/Electrophysiology Procedures and Post-Device/Electrophysiology Procedures.  Flexibility and comprehensiveness of this consolidated order set allows for these order sets to be used for the various applicable clinical situations.\n--a combination of input from the Cardiology Summit and expert advice from the KPNC Electrophysiology Service resulted in agreed upon clinical content and orders that would be applicable throughout KPNC\n--new order set was compared with other similar and related cardiac order sets (e.g. pre-cath, post-cath, pre-PCI, post-PCI, interfacility cardiac transport order set) to ensure consistency of orders and overall format among similar order sets\n--language at top of order set guides which hospitals can use the order set. Order set can be used throughout KPNC at hospital where it is appropriate to do so.\n\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nPhilip C. Lee, MD (Inpatient Health Connect Cardiology domain lead)\nMichael Lauer, M',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2206,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Phil Lee','',3098931,NULL,'OS NEw Cardio Peripheral Ultrafiltration',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',NULL,'SCL','L','N','H','S','Cardio Peripheral Ultrafiltration',NULL,'','','Emily Foo',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/4/09 Emailed comments to Weisshaar and Lee, due 5/8/09\r\n5/8/09 spreadsheet with changes from R&C sent to Sherry and Emily.  Due 5/11 for 5/13 advanced distribution.',NULL,'LIVE','