which occurs relatively frequently on the pediatric ward) has been extremely laborious with Health Connect given the number of very specialized diet, lab, poct, and insulin orders that they require.  This order set was constructed in order to both (a) streamline the admission process, and (b) standardize the orders according to best practices.  The hypoglycemia protocol supports the order set and contributes to patient safety.\n\nPhysician sponsor name:  Brian Cassidy, MD and Stevan Cavalier, MD\n\nDomain approving:  Regional Pediatric content team (led by Dr. Stevan Cavalier).\n\nThanks,\nBrian Cassidy, MD',NULL,'1202342470?P209674?Christie F Vidal\n\nReceived  paper orderset from Sherry Ellis and begining to build orderset.?1203313688?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\n2/8/08 released into WCR limited pilot. For regional governance process; sent for 2/20/08 CHIMP/P&T approval. Plan for 3/26/08 release pending regional approval.?1205166321?P209674?Christie F Vidal\n\nBuilt in Lead and sent to Stevan Caliver for review on next PHBS conference call. Emily Foo is reviewing Med section and making changes as needed.?1205779702?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nSherry Ellis/Stevan Cavalier phone mtg to finalize content?1212518210?K229966?Sherry J Ellis\n\nEmailed Dr. Brian Cassidy on 5/30 with screen shots of the hypoglycemia protocol and the section of nursing communication on this order set.  The goal is to reduce/ eliminate all of the nursing comm orders and house them in the protocol.  Requested a meeting with Dr. Cassidy to go through this consolidation together.  Waiting his response. se?1212526782?K229966?Sherry J Ellis\n\nDr. Cassidy returned my call, he is out of town this week.  States he hopes to view the documents I sent him at the end of this week or early next week.?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2210,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rob Norris','Jeff Klingman',2326672,NULL,'OS  tPA 414442, ICH 414356  revise per requirments and default SCDs',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',N