ULL,NULL,'Herb Szeto','',2452180,NULL,'OS NEW Adult Svcs: Ischemic Stroke Post tPA',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',NULL,'0','L','N','H','D','Ischemic Stroke Post tPA',NULL,NULL,'','Minh Nguyen',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','NEUR','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','Y',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','MEDSURG','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 12:14:01','2009-07-21 12:15:01','2009-07-28 16:14:51','2009-08-03 08:03:43','2008-04-01 17:15:16',' ',NULL,'','Anne Foss-Durrant','Herb Szeto',NULL,'','','',965,NULL,95,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-01-20 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-01-20 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-06-17 00:00:00','2009-05-20 00:00:00','2009-05-21 00:00:00','2009-06-04 00:00:00','2009-06-05 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-08 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-06-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-06-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-06-24 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-06-24 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-22 11:33:00','2009-06-17 01:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OS NEW Adult Svcs: Ischemic Stroke Post tPA (Related to SR# 3164160)\n\nI beleive that the original concern came from P&T regarding ASA and heparin after tPA for stroke.  In any event, I would like to create a post-TPA ischemic stroke orderset if a change request isnt already in the system.  It would be the same as the ischemic stroke orderset except:\nThe vital sign section should correspond to what is in the tPA orderset\nThe SQ heparin and aspirin would be defaulted to start 24-48 hours after tPA administration (i.e. QAM, skip next AM dose).  \nLovenox needs to be removed from the DVT prophalaxis section.\nCoumadin needs to be removed.\n\nThere also needs to be language to hold these two medications and notify MD  for any evidence of bleeding.  Lastly, there needs to be decision support language in the tPA orderset to use the post-tPA ischemic stroke orderset for admission.\n\n\nIve already discussed this with the HBS domain group.  Im waiting to hear back on 1 issue from Dr. Klingman of neurology.\n\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change:\nA separate post-tPA  stroke orderset has been created to minimize the risk of hemorrhagic complications.\n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\nThe use of anti-platelet agents and anticoagulation is different in stroke patients who have received t-PA compared to those who have not.  Although there is decision support in the current orderset highlighting such differences, there remained a potential to inadvertantly start these medications earlier than intended.  This new orderset is designed spefically to address those differences.\n\nNew Purpose and background added 5/8/09\n\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change:\nThis orderset is designed for the management of stroke patients who have received tPA and to minimize risk of bleeding in this population.\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\nThe HBS ischemic stroke orderset is currently used for all ischemic stroke patients.  Those patients',NULL,'1207676313?X441117?Jeremy D Vang\n\nTIGR reviewed.  Minh will seek confirmation from Dr. Seto before starting the built.?1207703486?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nemail to Dr. Szeto (M Nguyen) Regarding your request for a new Post-tPA Order Set.  Is it your intention that providers would always go to this new order set for post-tPA orders?  Currently, there is a Post-tPA section (mainly anti-platelets) on the Thrombolytics for Stroke order set.  Should this section be deleted once we have the new order set??1207752947?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nemail from Dr. Szeto: \nYes, the antiplatelet section should be deleted in the tPA orderset.  In the vast majority of cases, tPA will be given while the patient is in the ED.  The antiplatelet drugs wont be started until the patient get up to the ICU so those orders must be signed and held.  If they are in the tPA orderset, the provider must continue them at admission.  Moreover, they would need to remember not to reorder them on the standard stroke admission orderset.  This is why we decided to create a separate post-tPA stroke orderset. (See SR 2326672 for changes to ICH and Thrombolytics Order Sets)?1208544714?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nNOTE: per TIGR discussion 4/15/08, removing the antiplatelet orders from Thrombolytics order set is dependent upon having this new order set done. Plan to complete both and send for review/comment use.?1208882729?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nTIGR pending ClinCon build team creation of basic orders?1209515287?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nPaper mock up of order set sent to Dr. Szeto as initial draft. Pending review and changes, etc?1209571999?H521379?Tina H Hamilton\n\nH Szeto, requesting Neuro review, input. Edits to basic draft submitted per domain request.?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2244,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Vijay Rathore','',2466251,NULL,'NEW OS NEPH CRRT w/ Citrate for Anticoag',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',NULL,'SFO','L','N','H','S','CRRT',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'LIVE','Clo','NEP','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N','S',NULL,'NR',' ','N','MEDSURG','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-18 11:48:44','2009-04-21 11:49:44','2009-04-21 13:23:58','2009-04-24 08:58:59','2008-04-07 12:54:03',' ','Vijay Rathore','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',459,NULL,95,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-04-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-02-12 00:00:00','2009-02-17 00: