y the protocols called for nursing to calculate any dose adjustments.\nThe order sets and protocols were sent out for review by various stakeholders.\nSome pharmacists felt the protocol should be pharmacy driven rather than nursing driven.\nThe Critical Care Domain agreed with this proposal at their September 2nd meeting.\nThe proposal was taken to the IPDs peer group meeting after the CC domain meeting, and they proposed having nursing drive the protocol, but double check it with pharmacy.\nBoth proposals were discussed at the Regional Chiefs, and there was consensus that the Nurse Managers and MDs would prefer the protocol be pharmacy driven.\n\nThe question now is what is the next step?  Who is the correct person or group to make a final operational decision on this issue.  Once this has been resolved the order sets and protocols are ready to be released.\n\nThanks,\nKathy<BR><BR>2009-10-02 - Jung M Lee - See comments from Argatroban.  Leaning towards pharmacy-driven protocol.  Still need further workup and discussions to implement as pharmacy-driven protocol.<BR><BR>2009-10-06 - Jung M Lee - See comments from Argatroban SR 2563134.  From IPD meeting there was a consensus to move forward with pharmacy-driven protocol.  This will require multiple steps and training pharmacists in each facility which may take some time to implement.<BR><BR>2009-10-23 - Jung M Lee - Protocol in progress by IPD group.  Expect P&T approval around dec/jan.<BR><BR>2009-11-02 - Jung M Lee - Along with Argatroban protocol still being created by the IPD group.  Plan for P&T around dec/jan.  Final date to be determined.<BR><BR>2009-12-18 - Jung M Lee - llowed up on the status of pharmcy protocol with Doug OBrien.  The protocol is in the process of being drafted by SFO pharmacy group. Will follow up with SFO pharmacy group on the progress.<BR><BR>',984,1068,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2262,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',2546610,NULL,'OS NEW NeuroSURG: Neurosurgical Spinal Orders; create per attachme