re pedi ordersets.\n\nLInk should go at top of lab section in Seizures, Sepsis, Meningitis and LP ordersets - when they are all approved.  It reproduces what the state wants completed (their format).  The MD admitting the patient and completing the ordersets prints, completes and sends the form (usually with the specimen to the lab who then sends it on to the PHD).  \n\n\n\nOrder Set:\nLumbar Puncture Ped\nSeizure Ped\nSepsis\nMeningitis\n\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change: workflow\nAddition of California Encephalitis Project documentation and forms. \n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\nForms required by CA PHD when looking for viral causes of encephalitis such as West Nile Virus and Japenese Equine Encephalitis, among other causes\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nStevan Cavalier, MD\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\nPediatric Domain',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-28 - Sherry J Ellis - Emailed word document to Tina for formatting by Wendy Wibbens and then a URL to the clinical library. sellis<BR><BR>2008-08-29 - Tina H Hamilton - forwarded documents to Cynthia Rice for formatting.<BR><BR>2008-09-02 - Tina H Hamilton - pdf file received, formatted. Forwarded to Dr. Cavalier for approval to circulate, workflow, background/context.<BR><BR>2008-09-10 - Tina H Hamilton - 9/4 Dr Cavalier confirms file looks fine. Background/context and workflow missing.\nFollow up email to Dr. Cavalier sent on 9/10: with communication document draft\nThank you for confirming that the merged Ca Encephalitis Protocol looks OK. I can circulate to the live sites for review and comment as the first step in the regional governance process.\n\nBefore I do so, I need to have your information re: the background and context as well as the workflow and your approval of the communication document (where in the order set will the link be placed??).\nWill this be printed and completed by the physician on the unit and then sent to the State (and a copy scanned as part of the medical record)? Does this impact current workflows?\n\n Also, will check in with Marc Schiff re: how this document should be formatted. I assume that we are merely reproducing the document that the state provides; but need to ask if we need to also add the same page borders and space for patient name, etc since we are now hosting on KPHC especially if it will be completed and a coopy kept as a part of the medical record.  This information will accompancy the \"change\" through the governance process including presentation to the HCG and Med Exec committees. \n\n\n\nOrder Set:\nLumbar Puncture Ped\n\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change: workflow\nAddition of California Encephalitis Project documentation and forms. \n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\n<as provided by sponsor>\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nStevan Cavalier, MD\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\nPediatric Domain\n\n<BR><BR>2008-10-13 - Tina H Hamilton - 9/21/08: email from Dr. Cavalier, providing background/rationale\nOrder Set:\nLumbar Puncture Ped\nSeizure Ped\nSepsis\nMeningitis\n\nPer Marc Schiff\nTina,\nTook a quick look at the form.  My experience with other State mandated forms is that the State wants them to be generally formatted to their specifications.  However, in the past, they have let us add room for the patient identification and I would recommend that we do so with this form.\nThanks,\nMarc Schiff\n\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change: workflow\nAddition of California Encephalitis Project documentation and forms. \n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\nForms required by CA PHD when looking for viral causes of encephalitis such as West Nile Virus and Japenese Equine Encephalitis, among other causes\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nStevan Cavalier, MD\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\nPediatric Domain\n<BR><BR>2008-10-13 - Tina H Hamilton - Note to Dr Cavalier\nHi Dr. Cavalier,\nI heard from Dr. Schiff that the State sometimes allows us to create a space for patient identifiers on government forms and in this case he recommends we do so.\nSherry Ellis and I discussed this briefly today and have some questions:\n1> Will a copy of the submitted form be scanned and stored in KPHC? Are you keeping copies now? If so, what sort of patient identifier is on the original? (I stated in the communication document that a copy would be kept, but if this is not the current workflow, please let me know. Not sure in that case that we need a patient identifier...)\n\n2> How will we know when the State changes the forms? We can store what you provide, will the Pedi domain be responsible for letting KPHC know when forms are revised? If so, storing our own version makes sense. Otherwise, the State CEIP site has directions and the documents in pdf format. (I can see that having the documents merged into a single document and URL is easier than downloading and printing the individual forms found at the state site.)\n\n3> You mention below that this link would be in the order sets \"when they are all approved\". Are the ordersets currently under revision/creation so the timeline for the addition of the link is with their next version release? Or, is the addition of the link independent of other revision activities?\nMeningitis order set; partially built, not ready for governance\nSeptic shock; under revision, not yet sent for governance\nSeizure/Lumber Puncture: no draft build noted, are these under revision?\n\nThank you,\n\nTina Herrmann Hamilton, RN, BSN, PHN<BR><BR>2009-04-16 - Sean E Ryan - sent out email to Dr. Cavalier and Tina: \n\nIm just starting to look at the SR SR# CHG000002875281 - Pediatric California Encephilitis Project documentation; add a hyperlink with documentation.  I know this is from a while ago but its low priority has kept it on the back burner. \n\nI see a lot of correspondence has happened with you and Tina. Where is this project and how can we get it done. \n\nThank you,<BR><BR>',459,459,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2300,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rob Norris','',2887413,NULL,'OS Rev ED Asthma COPD orderset 414295',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','R','H','D','Asthma/COPD ED',NULL,NULL,'','Chris Vidal',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NOWRK','Wor','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','ED','CC','ED','ED','ISERV','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2010-01-20 13:44:10','2010-02-23 13:45:10',NULL,'2009-12-22 12:04:46','2008-09-03 15:54:28',' ',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,'','','',981,NULL,201,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-14 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-01-20 00:00:00','2009-12-16 00:00:00','2009-12-21 00:00:00','2010-01-08 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-01-11 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-01-13 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-01-25 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-01-27 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-01-27 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-01 10:25:00','2010-06-14 01:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SSC ED-Approved by ED Domain:  Request to update/change Orderset 414295\n\nword doc attached\n\nName of Order Set:	\nED Asthma and COPD Order Set 865\n\nPurpose/intent of order set change:\n	Intent of orderset change is to streamline and update the orderset content, as well as take advantage of new orderset functionality (PRL).\n\nBackground information/context setting:\n	The current orderset has separate sections for adults and pediatric patients, which can be combined and configured 