group in SCAL regarding restraints in which all restraint request can be reviewed.<BR><BR>2008-10-03 - Denise M Seymour - Reviewed in Issue Mgmt Mtg: Pending R&D from workgroup. Deltese to contact Mary to find out status of workgroup.<BR><BR>2008-10-06 - Deltese L Duncan - This request involves when an order is placed for restraints and soon to expire. The requestor wants an alert to appear with this notification retraint order soon to retire when the nurse opens the patients chart.\n\nThis alert will not be triggered from documentation in a flowsheet row and does not require iNGG approval.  No follow up from Mary required.\n\nRequest needs to be reviewed/approved  by the orders team.<BR><BR>2008-10-15 - Deltese L Duncan - This request will be reviewed in the next NCC SR review meeting with Management on 10/21/08 for approval of a nursing alert being attached to restraint orders when placed.<BR><BR>2008-10-21 - Denise M Seymour - Issue Mgmt 10/21: Lisa R. will follow-up w/ClinCon team to find out if BPA can fire from restraint order after 24hrs. IF so, this will be assigned to the ORders team.<BR><BR>2008-10-28 - Denise M Seymour - ISSUE Mgmt 10/28: This ticket has been approved for build work. May need to work with Epic. Attach e-mail from Aditi that provides more info.<BR><BR>2008-10-30 - Denise M Seymour - Lisa R. to attach e-mail with more information.<BR><BR>2008-11-04 - Denise M Seymour - Nurse Facility Lead SR Review Mtg 10/30/08: There is possibly a small workgroup looking into this.<BR><BR>2008-11-10 - Denise M Seymour - Aditi Vakil/CA/KAIPERM \n09/30/2008 05:16 PM\nTo: Lisa Rohr/CA/KAIPERM@Kaiperm \ncc: Deltese Duncan/CA/KAIPERM@KAIPERM, Denise Seymour/CA/KAIPERM@KAIPERM \nSubject Re: Remedy 2209859 \n  \n \nMaybe for the first and yes for the second. Someone from Clindoc team would need to work with Epic TS for the first item. The second one is very do-able :-)\n\n-------\nLisa Rohr/CA/KAIPERM \n09/30/2008 05:13 PM\nTo : Aditi Vakil/CA/KAIPERM@KAIPERM \nc