tent:\nGI SUIT',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2351,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'HCG recommendation 12/17/08','',3359095,NULL,'OS Multiple - PT/INR Reconfigure: INR: On warfarin, INR: No warfarin therapy',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'L','R','M','D','PT/INR',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'As shown on HCG approved changes for Arrythmia ED orderset. Lorna Yamaguchi seeking ICU domain OK< but suggests that Phil Lee and Herb Szeto confirm needed build. See email sent 12/18/09 to Phil Lee and Herb Szeto. \r\n\r\n\r\n1/5/09 follow up note to all above, asking for rationale and approval in absence of any comments from Trevor, et al\r\n\r\n\r\n12/23/09 Phil Lee\r\nby the way, I actually prefer the \"INR\" label for the lab....on some order sets, it says \"PT\" and others \"PT/INR\"...we should standardize them all the same way on all the order sets.\r\n',NULL,'NICE','Wor','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','MEDSURG','CCARE','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-22 12:04:56','2009-02-11 12:57:52',' ',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,'','','',959,NULL,95,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-18 10:34:00','2009-02-17 11:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OS Multiple - PT/INR Reconfigure: INR: On warfarin, INR: No warfarin therapy\n\nApproved by HCG 12.17.09 based upon review of revised CVA/TIA Initial Evaluation orderset. This will relieve the need for a hard stop in orders. \n\nPer Herb Szeto\nIm in agreement with this change.  We asked for the removal of the question altogether we we wrote these ordersets and never got a satisfactory reason of why it is required.  The result level that triggers a call for a critical value is independent of whether the patient is on warfarin and Im not aware that the lab processes the speciment any differently based on the answer.  In any case, we probably need to understand why this question is being asked in the first place to address Phils comment.  Id personally prefer - On warfarin and No warfarin therapy since it would include everyone, but can live with the current options if it means not having to go back through HCG.\n\n\n\n\nRationale per Philip Lee\n\nthis is certainly ok for all order sets that I work on/am responsible for.\n\nthe term \"no anticoagulants\" may be misleading...what they really mean is \"not on warfarin\"....however, they could be on other anticoagulants like lovenox which does not affect the INR...and it is still appropriate to check that button.\n\ni think it is fine re: PT/INR orders.\n\nwe should not be ordering any aPTT labs anymore. it has been my intent to review order sets with aPTT to see if most (if not all) can be removed).\n\nin KPNC, we no longer use aPTT to follow heparin dosing...rather, anti-Xa assay for this. as a result, no baseline aPTT needs to be drawn either.\n\nthere is a rare time that we will check a baseline aPTT in evaluation for hypercoagulable state, but this is relatively uncommon and can be ordered ala carte when needed.',NULL,'1260307365ï££W508677ï££Status changed to WorkInProgress as Task CHG000004284081 has begun work.ï£¢',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-11 - Tina H Hamilton - PMO notes imported\nAs shown on HCG approved changes for Arrythmia ED orderset. Lorna Yamaguchi seeking ICU domain OK< but suggests that Phil Lee and Herb Szeto confirm needed build. See email sent 12/18/09 to Phil Lee and Herb Szeto. \n\n\n1/5/09 follow up note to all above, asking for rationale and approval in absence of any comments from Trevor, et al \n\n\n12/23/09 Phil Lee \nby the way, I actually prefer the \"INR\" label for the lab....on some order sets, it says \"PT\" and others \"PT/INR\"...we should standardize them all the same way on all the order sets. \n\n\nRemedy ticket created, note to build/orders team to ID impacted ordersets<BR><BR>2009-02-17 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, requires lab review. Plan, send to Ted Lynch for regional lab review.<BR><BR>2009-02-17 - Tina H Hamilton - Sent note with request to Fran Strychaz (cc Ted Lynch) for review by lab committee.<BR><BR>2009-02-18 - Tina H Hamilton - Fran Strychaz forwarded question to lab goverance (Thomas Lorey, David Levy, Robert X Greenberg<BR><BR>2009-02-19 - Tina H Hamilton - email from Dave Levy\nI looked closer and think I see why the lab may actually be the ones who requested anticoagulation status as a question.  It looks to me like it crosses the interface and gets picked up and presented with returned results.  Thus on the patient below I can see the result of the PT/INR and that the patient is anticoagulated on warfarin.  This is probably a good thing, so we dont have to search elsewhere for this important info. \n\nI recommend that we ask Herb to do what the ED has done and have orders that fill in the 2 most common options so the docs do not get stopped and have to - those would be PT/INR Baseline and PT/INR on Warfarin.\n\nSee my screenshot below to see what I am talking about on the results side.  Herb - can you agree with this?\n\n<BR><BR>2009-03-03 - Tina H Hamilton - aproved for swap on surgical order sets per Maggie Mentakis at TIGR meeting.<BR><BR>2009-03-12 - Tina H Hamilton - Inquiry sent to Fran Strychaz re: lab committee approval status<BR><BR>2009-03-20 - Tina H Hamilton - Herb Szeto inquiring re: status, He prefers;\nINR- Not taking warfarin (rather than currently on no anticoagulants)\nINR - On warfarin \nas the two options but to leave the two options as is if it required that we take back through HCG.\n\nFollow up email to Fran Strychaz and Dave Levy (cc Herb Szeto) re: status of lab committee approval and options for selection.<BR><BR>2009-03-26 - Tina H Hamilton - email from Herb Szeto to include HBS Atrial Fibrillation orderset as well.\n\nNote, per Tina HH, this change will require and extract to identify impacted ordersets and obtain domain approval to change or exclude from the change.<BR><BR>2009-03-26 - Tina H Hamilton - copied Fran Strychaz with above note, gentle reminder that we are still awaiting lab committee approval.<BR><BR>2009-03-27 - Tina H Hamilton - Recieved out of office response from Fran Strchaz, referring questions to Jeffrey M Hoffman moving forward, Note to Jeffrey Hoffman inquiring as to status.<BR><BR>2009-03-30 - Tina H Hamilton - email Jeffrey M Hoffman\nDue to recent changes in LWG leadership- -Dr. Levy passed the torch to Dr. Tom Lorey, Regional Lab Director- -we used our time in March to meet and determine a transition plan rather than hold the LWG as usual.  Therefore this issue has not yet been discussed.  We do, however, plan to reconvene the group in April and I will make sure that this is one of the topics on our agenda.\n<BR><BR>2009-03-31 - Tina H Hamilton - email agreement from Dave Levy, Tom Lorey and Herb Szeto to move forward.\nMap \"INR - No Warfarin Therapy\" to Baseline\nOptions for selection will be\n1) \"INR - No Warfarin therapy\" (mapped to Baseline)\n2) \"INR - On Warfarin\". (mapped to Warfarin)\n\nemail to Rob Norris, Lorna Yamaguchi, Maggie Mentakis, Elliiot Morrison and Jaya Mokkapati to change across domain ordersets.<BR><BR>2009-03-31 - Tina H Hamilton - Pending review by Mark Knoblauch, extract, and assignment to the appropriate build AC.<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - PeriOp domain approval to make change across Surgical (PeriOp and PostOP) ordersets.<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - email Dave Levy\nI think that the discussion is that ordersets should have INR on Warfarin and INR baseline in the same language and fashion as was done for the ED folks on their orderset.  Tom Lorey can give formal approval if that is what is needed by whatever process he feels is necessary here.  I think that if Herb and the ED Suite lead (cannot remember his name right now) agree, then probably worth doing this for all.  Tom Lorey the regional lab director is now leading the lab group and I am a part of his team, so I do not want to overstep here.\n\n\nI agree with Tom - baseline or none is probably best.  Maybe \"baseline\" is not so bad because it is fairly noncommital and would be closest to the idea of \"no warfarin\".  Probably covers 99% of the clinical scenarios that we care about.\n\n(For example:  Patients with DIC or severe liver disease with abnormal PT/INR would then have something that showed that their values were measured on no anticoagulation).<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - Note to Herb Szeto copying distribution list to confirm which lab orders are impacted; accompanied with screen shot of PT EAP record associated with varying display names (PT, PT/INR, etc). Are we now substituting PT with INR or only making this change when the display name is TP/INR or INR?<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - email Dave Levy\nI think that the key is that all single orders need to be replaced by 2 possibilities - PT/INR on warfarin and PT/INR on no warfarin therapy - as long as both of those choices replace a single choice on every order set, then I think we are ok and have made progress, allowing the clinician to answer the question by selecting proper choice instead of having to be stopped and answer the question\n\nApproved by Tom Lorey<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - secondary note per Phil Lee\nAlso, Phil asked if we could float the secondary request to the group, and that is, to review all ordersets and remove the aPTT and PTT orders as obtaining this baseline is no longer clinically useful (except in the case of hypercoagulapathy so on ordersets specific for that, leave the aPTT or PTT orders).\nIf this is agreed by the domains, we could do a consistent across the domain review of ordersets and update. \nThis may be considered a HIGH level change since it involves removing content that has been approved. We would need to circulate for review and comment and bring to the HCG after the domains agreed to this change.\n\nPhil Lee\nas a point of clarification, for KPNC, we NO LONGER use PTT to adjust heparin dosing. Rather, we use anti-Xa. \n\nAs a reflex (ie fall back to previous practices), physicians routinely check off PT/INR and PTT....in case heparin might be used later. there is no value in checking baseline PTT (or anti-Xa for that matter) prior to initiation of heparin. \n\nthis is the rationale for the suggestion.\n\n(This is a high level change that will require a separate SR. Tina HH to create)<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - Change to PT/INR orders approved by Elliot Morrison (via email)\nApproved by Maggie Mentakis, email\nApproved by Herb Szeto, email<BR><BR>2009-04-06 - Tina H Hamilton - email Rob Norris\nyes, so approved-- chief among them would be the STEMI and chest pain ordersets, GI Bleed, Alcohol with Complications; Im sure there are others.\n<BR><BR>2009-05-29 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Met with Britt Mattern about the extraction and discovered a streamlined approach to finding the list of order sets with aPTT/PTT.<BR><BR>2009-06-19 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Lists of Order sets by domain sent to domain leads to determine which order sets to change.  See master list of ordersets attachment.<BR><BR>2009-08-03 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - As of 8/3/09, the Periop, Perinatal, ED, Med Surg and IS domains have submitted their lists of which order sets to make the changes to.  Emailed Pediatric and Critical Care domains requesting reply by 8/14/09 or we will assume that they agree to the changes.\n\nNote that anti-Xa will be added to order set 414314 ED Immediate Action Orthopedic order set and 414290 Altered level of Consciousness ED.<BR><BR>2009-08-27 - Tina H Hamilton - Sent domain reminder to L Yamguchi that approval is pending for critical care order sets.<BR><BR>2009-12-08 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Status changed to WorkInProgress as Task CHG000004284081 has begun work.<BR><BR>2009-12-15 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Requests for final approval of changes sent to domain leaders of IS, ED, Periop, M/S and Crit Care with the final list of changes to be made. Responses due by 12/29/09.  Final change will be implemented on 1/26/10.<BR><BR>',984,984,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2352,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Dan Brugger','',3201970,NULL,'Changes to Standard Admission PICU OS',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',NULL,'0','L','R','H','D','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Pen','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','Resource Assignment','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','PICU','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2010-02-17 16:55:40','2010-03-23 16:56:40',NULL,'2009-12-22 12:04:57','2008-12-17 15:44:40',' ',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,'','','',993,NULL,201,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL