rescription printing works as advertised.  Ive had a few occasions to use it, and the paper is ready and waiting at the IT printer.  Hopefully we wont have any more remodelling :)\n\nNow that thats done, we have another request, one which may be felt to be an enhancement, but one we know is possible, as they have this capability in Hawaii.  Im going to attach an e-mail from Christina Shih to Britt Matern and Andre Santana sent 3 months ago; item #2 is the one Im discussing here (but the others are also languishing).\n\nEssentially what wed like is a button for the \"Class\" field, to be able to click \"Outside Fill\" instead of having to click on the little magnifying glass and select it via scrolling down.  If you look at the screenshot, it actually may not be exactly what we want here (though may be OK).  In our current functionality, the default setting is to \"Discharge\"-- this may be the same as \"Fill Now\".  Whatever the case, we really only need two options:  Discharge (or Fill Now), and Outside Fill.  The default setting should remain \"Discharge\".\n\nThe above represents current functionality which we would like, and the MDs here and ones I interact with regionally cant understand (from a technological standpoint) why Hawaii is able to have this and Northern CA does not.\n\nHaving said the above, in a perfect world we would like to be able to hit one button only for all meds ordered as outpatient prescriptions, without having to open up each medication to change it to \"Outside Fill\" in such laborious fashion.  This adds up if you have someone who tells you theyve run out of the 8 medications they take on a daily basis, and could you please refill them, but give me a paper prescription please?  I realize this last item may be an enhancement request, but Ill t',NULL,'1210023141ï££I591970ï££Daria L Rosen\n\nPer Roylyn Fernandez, Nursing Content does not own this portion of the build as described by Ryan Lambertï£¢',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-05 - Daria L Rosen - 