hen test the note within the log and NOT from activity to see if the tourniquet values appear on note.\n<BR><BR>2009-07-02 - Jeremy D Vang - Test case #36805 in GGM instance.  Entered tourniquet date and time to inflation and deflation and accepted the note.   Went to test the dot phrase \".ORTOURNTIME\" in a regular note, inside a pt chart.  NO results came through, then went to test the same dot phrase inside the note in the log and the results came through. (see attachment \"General\" for my findings).<BR><BR>2009-07-24 - Jeremy D Vang - Sent email to Epic email, asking why tourniquet time is ONLY able to pull inside the log and NOT outside the log?  Epics response, \"The OpTime SmartLinks work by finding the first surgical log that is linked to the admission (Hospital Chart) that the user is accessing.  In this test case, there are multiple logs (ORL records) linked to this patients Hospital Encounter, and the SmartLink only displays information for the first one, which is actually ORL 36813.  If you would document tourniquet information in that log, it should display in the SmartLink.  I hope that helps, let me know if you have additional questions.\"\n\nNext step is to retest tourniquet time to see if results carry over within same encounter like epic mentioned.\n<BR><BR>2009-08-06 - Jeremy D Vang - 8/6/06 - Next step need to have lead show and test to see if theres a (null) value and retest the tourniquet time.<BR><BR>2009-08-20 - Jeremy D Vang - 8/20/09 - Got replied from Chris Russell. \"Unfortunately, there are no parameters available in the ORTOURNTIME SmartLink.  We can make an enhancement request for such a parameter in our next release.\" \n\nNext step:  Need to continue building a new \"Orthopedic Brief Operative Note\" and informed Maggie about epics finding.\n\n8/19/09 - Sherry and I tried to find paramaters on the back end to see if we have add a \"null\" value around tourniquet time.  We have NO success and contacted Chris Russel from EPIC.  He wi