,'2009-09-22 00:00:00','2009-10-06 00:00:00','2009-10-07 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-11-09 00:00:00','2009-11-09 00:00:00','2009-11-11 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-10-12 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-11-23 00:00:00','2009-11-23 00:00:00','2009-11-25 00:00:00','2009-11-25 00:00:00','2009-11-25 00:00:00','2009-11-25 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-09 03:35:00','2009-11-25 08:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Update medication section on Day of Surgery ORTHO NCAL 414208\n\nPurpose/Intent of new order set or change:\nUpdate and organize Pre-emptive Analgesic sectioon to include 3 single selection groups for apap, nsaids, and narcotics.\n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\nProvide more choices for pre-emptive analgesia.\n\nPhysician Sponsor:\nJohn Woll, WCR, Ortho\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\nSurg/Ortho',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-10 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR team review\nThis SR is submitted in advance of final content. Dr. Woll to provide final content upon SUIT agreement.<BR><BR>2009-04-08 - Thomas Chun - version 2 submitted to J.Woll for review today. please see attachment.<BR><BR>2009-07-20 - Thomas Chun - emailed updated change to j.woll. please see attachment from today.  awaiting feedback.<BR><BR>2009-08-12 - Thomas Chun - 2nd email to j.woll today (4th contact attempt [1 previous phone call l/m & 1 IM])\n\nReturn Receipt\nYour document:	Outstanding build requests SR 3808527 & 3350732\nwas received by:	John Woll/CA/KAIPERM\nat:	08/12/2009 01:41:49 PM\n<BR><BR>2009-09-02 - Thomas Chun - d/w j.woll this afternoon and he approves the screen shots.<BR><BR>2009-09-04 - Thomas Chun - approved by j.woll - on track for oct HCG<BR><BR>2009-09-10 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Sent to Maggie Mentakis and Marla Gonzales for domain approval to circulate SUIT content.  Reply due by 9/15/09.  Will send for review and comment if no response by 9/15/09.<BR><BR>2009-09-21 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Second request for approval from Maggie Mentakis sent 9/17/09.<BR><BR>2009-09-22 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Approval from Maggie: This looks fine to me.  As long as the orders are written in a timely fashion there should be minimal impact to the periop nurses.  Pharmacy may need to stock the preop pyxis machines with these meds if they are highly utilized so there needs to be a heads up to them.\nMarla Gonzales (Nursing) approved also.<BR><BR>2009-09-22 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Sent for review and comment, due 10/6/09.  Plan for HCG on 10/21/09 and release 11/24/09.<BR><BR>2009-10-07 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Comments sent to Dr. Woll for resonse/rationale due 10/12/09<BR><BR>2009-10-13 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - No response from Dr. Woll; planned HCG changed to 11/18/09 and release 12/22/09.  Still waiting for response from Dr. Woll to comments.<BR><BR>2009-11-13 - Tina H Hamilton - Retroactive comment; OS not approved at HCG due to questions related to use of Celebrex and Oxycontin. Follow up telephone call with Dr Woll indicates OS to be rescheduled for 11/18 when he can attend; and reviewed with Trupti Mehta, regional P&T in advance of HCG.<BR><BR>2009-11-13 - Tina H Hamilton - Phone mtg, John Woll and Trupti Mehta; use of meds is part of an IP multimodal analgesia regimine, review of literature. Agreements to add decision support:\nAdd Decision Support to preemptive ONE time meds\nCelecoxib (Celebrex) should only be used in patients receiving pharmacologic VTE prophylaxis postoperatively\nMorphine SR (MS Contin) is the preferred long acting narcotic. Oxycodone is intended for use by In Patients who have treatment failure or allergy/intolerance to morphine SR (MS Contin/Oramorph SR).\n\nConcerns re: long term post op use of these meds expressed, so agreement to add decision support to the ortho pain med modules, created separate SR \nCelecoxib (Celebrex) should only be used in patients receiving pharmacologic VTE prophylaxis post operatively.\n	Set default dose 200 mg, once daily for 3 days\nAdd decision support to ATC Pain Meds,\nMorphine SR (MS Contin) is the preferred long acting narcotic. Oxycodone is intended for use by In Patients who have treatment failure or allergy/intolerance to morphine SR (MS Contin/Oramorph SR).\nNew screen shots to be sent, Trupti to review with P&T colleagues and let Dr Woll know of decision.<BR><BR>2009-11-13 - Tina H Hamilton - Screen shots sent. Trupti questions changes. Dr Woll responds with agreements to changes as shown in screen shots. Dr.Woll requests that Day of Surgery labs be added \nWe should add a labs section with three entries in this order, but none of them pre-checked:\n\nPT/INR, Collect now - STAT\nCBC w/o diff, Collect now - STAT\nChem 7, Collect now - STAT\n\nApproved by Maggie Mentakis.\nAlso, move Celebrex to last position.<BR><BR>2009-11-13 - Tina H Hamilton - Added attachment,most current screenshots.<BR><BR>2009-11-13 - Christie F Vidal - Made lab changes to Ortho Day of Surgery orderset per Dr. Wolls request. attached latest screen shots to ticket.<BR><BR>2009-11-18 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Approved at HCG on 11/18/09 with the following changes:  \n-In the Around the Clock Pain (ORTHO) section add \"Oxymorphone (Opana) is the preferred alternative long acting narcotic \" under the sentence about Morphine SR is the preferred long acting narcotic.\n-Change \"…intolerance to morphine SR (MS Contin/Oramorph SR).\" to \"…intolerance to morphine SR (MS Contin/Oramorph SR) and oxymorphone (Opana).\n-Add Oxymorphone (Opana), pharmacist to confirm dose and frequency\n-Change order of meds to: Morphine SR, Oxymorphone, Oxycodone, Acetominophen, NORCO, PERCOCET\n\nScheduled for release 12/22/09\n<BR><BR>2009-11-18 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Previous comment is an error.  Approved by HCG on 11/18/09 with no changes.  Scheduled for release on 12/22/09.<BR><BR>2009-12-22 - Christie F Vidal - Maker-Chris Vidal<BR><BR>2009-