here are 2 related SRs: CHG000003425624 and CHG000003425701',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-10 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, domain approved by Herb Szeto.  Assigned to Chris Vidal pending resource assignment.<BR><BR>2009-03-10 - Tina H Hamilton - Note, there are 2 related SRs: CHG000003425624 and CHG000003425701\n\nemail from Herb Szeto:\nBelow is the text of the original request.  The second SR applies to what is highlighted red.  Moreover, it appears that the text that is in the SR that you sent me is somewhat different from what was originally submitted.  For instance, the SR that you sent me screens everyone over the age of 60 OR BMI<18 whereas the original criteria was everyone with BMI<18.5.  Im concerned that we will be ordering alot more albulmins that we need to with the revised criteria.  In any case, it should be OK as long as we are able to discuss with the AC at the time of the build to fine tune.\n\nCHG000003425624\nCHG000003425701\n\n1)  Using PRL functionality have a lab order for albumin and Pre-albumin show up defaulted in the HBS admission and rounding ordersets if ONE of the following criteria are met:   (Patients who have had those labs done in the last month should be excluded.)\na patients BMI is <18.5.  OR\na patient has had greater than a 10% drop in weight defined as (Highest recorded weight in the last year - current weight)/current weight > 10%\n\nAs a prerequisite to the above request, those labs would need to be added to those ordersets with NEXT AM as the frequency\nIf this is not possible then build a BPA that would alert the MD to order those labs when the criteria are met.  The BPA should be embedded into the admission and rounding navigators.\n\n\n2)  Create a BPA that would direct the MD to enter Protein Calorie Malnutrition in the Problem List. if  BOTH of the following criteria were met: (Must have one from #1 and # from #2)\n1.	Albumin <3 OR Pre-Albumin <12\n2.	BMI<18.5 OR patient has had greater than a 10% drop in weight\n\nCu