tions','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','M','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','CCARE','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-12-16 16:26:19','2010-01-26 14:18:16',NULL,'2009-12-22 12:05:37','2009-03-10 16:20:16',' ',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,'','','',965,NULL,201,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-17 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2009-12-16 00:00:00','2009-11-18 00:00:00','2009-09-04 00:00:00','2009-09-18 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2009-12-07 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2009-12-09 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2009-12-21 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2009-12-23 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2009-12-23 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-13 07:36:00','2009-12-16 03:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OS NEW ICU Therapeutic Hypothermia Order Set: Regional Critical Care Domain SR\n\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change:\nTo standardize delivery of therapeutic hypothermia after cardiac arrest.\n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\nThereapuetic hypothermia after cardiac arrest has been recommended since the 2005 AHA Guidelines but infrequently administered. The medication and laboratory order entry is facilitated by an order set.\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nGreg Marelich, MD, Pulmonary and Critical Care Medicine, SSC\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\nCritical Care Team\n\nSynonyms, 11/24/09 per Lorna Yamaguchi\nICU\nED\nCardiac Arrest\nArrest\nHypothermia\nTHACA \nPost-cardiac arrest',NULL,'1248898280ï££K229966ï££Sherry Ellis\n\nCreating dependent related Change Requestï£¢1261506005ï££O899477ï££Status changed to WorkInProgress as Task CHG000004352692 has begun work.ï£¢',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-17 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, assigned to build team, pending resouce assignment<BR><BR>2009-04-15 - Jeremy D Vang - Start the nut shell for medications to start.<BR><BR>2009-05-27 - Jeremy D Vang - Requested for new EAP, \"Initaite Therapeutic Hypothermia Protocol\" . Starting on protocol doc for URL.<BR><BR>2009-06-18 - Jeremy D Vang - Finished lab build in prod. Next step is follow up w/ the requested eap and take screen shot for first stage of dance process.<BR><BR>2009-06-19 - Jeremy D Vang - Finished lab. Went through Brian meeting. Still waiting on the new EAP porotocol.  Need to put a place holder while waiting for the new EAP.  To send out screen shot.<BR><BR>2009-06-26 - Jeremy D Vang - Put place holder while waiting for the new EAP.  To follow up w/ Sherry/Markon new EAP.<BR><BR>2009-07-14 - Jung M Lee - Rx build updated based on Dr Marelichs comments.  Updating the therapeutic hypothermia protocol weblink.<BR><BR>2009-07-21 - Jung M Lee - verifying build with Dr Marelich/Dr Cheng.  Awaiting response regarding the following:\n1) Do you want the physicians to acknowledge the inclusion and exclusion criteria by putting a hard stop?  (similar to tpa order set where you would have to answer Yes or No to each criteria)\n\n2) Do we want more specific titration information for nurses on fentanyl, versed, and cisatracurium infusions in the admin instruction (something similar to ven-sed order set)? \n\n3) Just to clarify, are the morphine, versed, and vecuronium IV push orders to be used ONLY prior to getting the infusion started?  Then would it make more sense to build these like a one-time dose as a bolus prior to starting the infusion rather than using \"q1h prn\" or \"q30min prn\" frequencies and stating in the admin instruction \"discontinue during rewarming phase\"? \n\n<BR><BR>2009-07-27 - Jung M Lee - No response on the build questions yet.  Emailed Dr Marelich again regarding the build questions.<BR><BR>2009-07-29 - Sherry Ellis - Sherry Ellis\n\nCreating dependent related Change Request<BR><BR>2009-07-30 - Jung M Lee - Response from Dr Marelich:\nI really dont think people will be using these orders without reading the inclusion/exclusion criteria. This is too novel, and yet some physicians may stretch the indications (like using it on gravid patients, which has been done with good results). We havent done hard stops with sepsis or HAMP ordersets... I wouldnt use them here.\n\nI can agree to std fentanyl and midazolam rates - like 25mcg/hr and 2 mg/hr. That would probably work for 80%.\nThe morphine, versed and vec were supposed to be \"ED IVP only\" so the one-time dose approach might work out fine. If they dont start the gtts in an hour, though it might pose a problem, and an hour goes by quickly in the ED or ICU. Is there was an option to preset the order for q 1hr prn 2 doses each ? That would be better, if possible.<BR><BR>2009-07-31 - Jeremy D Vang - Jung and I are about 80% completed.  Still fine tuning the meds and lab with Dr. Marelich.  Next step, waiting for EAP to be activated and send protocol for URL.<BR><BR>2009-08-04 - Jung M Lee - Resending protocol document to Dr Marelich for review.  Modified original protocol document to include additional IVP medications (versed, morphine, vecuronium) and recommending to include specific rates to the sed/hyp/nmba infusion orders specified in the protocol.<BR><BR>2009-08-06 - Jung M Lee - Protocol document reviewed by Dr Marelich.  Response from Dr Marelich:\ncould you please be sure to change the fentanyl gtt to 25 mcg/hr fixed dose, and the midazolam gtt to 2 mg/hr fixed dose in the orders? I see that its been changed in the protocol checklist.\n\nI agree with your edit,\"Witnessed cardiac arrest or known down time less than 15 min (defined as time from cardiac arrest onset to initiation of ACLS, excluding bystander CPR or “found down” of unknown duration)\"\n\nI like what you did with the morphine/midazolam/vec for the ED. Thats very practical now.\n\nSince I submitted this for build, the regional critical care group was shooting for glucose control under 140; we are now shooting for under 180 due to more recent literature. \nCan you please change the Call Physician order AND the protocol document to reflect this higher value?<BR><BR>2009-08-06 - Jung M Lee - Emailed Dr Marelich again for clarification on sed/analg rates.  Also getting clarification on NMBA monitoring for nursing.<BR><BR>2009-08-11 - Jung M Lee - Response from Dr Marelich:\n\n1. Practically, we arent giving instructions on how long to titrate midaz and fent to RASS<-3 prior to cisatracurium start, and I dont want to spend a whole bunch of time doing it either. How about changing the protocol from:\n\nCURRENT:\n? Start Midazolam infusion at 2 mg/hr and Fentanyl infusion at 25 mcg/hr. Once adequate doses are established to RASS< -3, determine TOF.  Start Cisatracurium infusion at 2 mcg/kg/hr, titrating to TOF ¼.  \n\nPROPOSED CHANGE:\n? Start Midazolam infusion at 2 mg/hr and Fentanyl infusion at 25 mcg/hr and rapidly adjust to goal of RASS< -3, then start Cisatracurium infusion at 2 mcg/kg/hr, titrating to TOF ¼.  Once Cisatracurium infusion started, maintain rate of Midazolam and Fentanyl infusions.  \n\nI am pretty sure that will do the trick. \n\n2. All ICUs, in my opinion, should have a NMBA policy about using TOF for titration, theres no other practical way to do it. \n\n3. We ought to have the NG tube order present (but un-checked, as a large number of pts will come through the ED and have an order there or with the admit order set). Can you slip the NG tube order in after the PO meds so that physicians will realize that an enteral route is needed?\n\nWill modify the order set based on his response.\n<BR><BR>2009-08-11 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, confirmed plans for review and comment following sponsor approval; HCG 9/22/09.<BR><BR>2009-08-11 - Jung M Lee - Plan for full screen shot to Dr Marelich tomorrow.  Planning for september HCG<BR><BR>2009-08-12 - Jung M Lee - Dr Cheng agrees to change the following verbiage thats part of the inclusion criteria:\nFrom \"?Return of normal rhythm (VF, pulseless VT, asystole, PEA) < 30 min\" to \"Return of normal rhythm from cardiac arrest (VF, pulseless VT, asystole, PEA) less than 30 min\"<BR><BR>2009-08-13 - Jung M Lee - Complete screen shot sent out to sponsors yesterday.  Response:\n\nCriteria\n\"Return of normal rhythm from cardiac arrest (VF, pulseless VT, asystole, PEA) less than 30 minutes\" is an improvement, but how about using the more common clinical terminology, \"Return of spontaneous circulation within 30 minutes of cardiac arrest\" ?\n\nNotification/Call If\nFirst two orders, \"degree\" should be \"degrees\"\nThird order, \"... for potassium less than 3.2 (goal potassium = 3.5 or greater during cooling)\" could be, \"...for potassium during cooling less than 3.2 (goal potassium during cooling is 3.5 or greater)\"\n\nMeds\nlook good to me, thanks for working in the NG tube\n\nLabs\nAll labs should be checked.\nLabs for start of protocol - are they preset to 1 occurrence each? PT/PTT need not be preset to presence or absence of anticoagulation. The comment for each order should read, \"Draw and send labs at the start of the protocol,\" instead of \"...Draw and send labs...\" Lactate dehydrogenase should be lactate (lactic acid)\nLabs every 6 hours - are they preset to 4 occurrences each? The comments for all 3 labs should read, \"every 6 hours for the first 24 hours\" Lactate dehydrogenase should be lactate (lactic acid)\nLabs every 8 hours - are they preset to 3 occurrences each? The comments for all 4 orders should read \"every 8 hours for the first 24 hours\"<BR><BR>2009-08-13 - Jung M Lee - Second revised screen shot sent to Dr Cheng and Marelich<BR><BR>2009-08-14 - Jung M Lee - More feedback from the screen shot:\nThe q 4hr x 24hr glucose POCT order turned into an iSTAT order. It should be changed back to a POCT order.\n\nWe need a urine pregnancy test (unchecked) to be obtained at the start of the protocol. I would say keep this unselected. \n\nDoes anyone have any thoughts about the \"start of protocol\" CBC, chem7, ca,mg,phos and PT/PTT being all \"collect now-stat\" x 1 occurrence and the remainder of the \"start of protocol\" labs like trop I, lactate, UPT, ABGs and fibrinogen, be \"collect now-routine\"? Seems to me that a nurse will be busy enough packing ice and doesnt need the clicks to release all these lab slips. Sorry I didnt recognize that sooner.<BR><BR>2009-08-17 - Jeremy D Vang - 8/16/09 - Sponsor approved v4 screens shot\n8/14/09 - Sent Dr. Marelich screen shot of v4 for review on labs changes. \n\nNext step: Waiting for background info from sponsor and lead to QA, then send to gov for R&C.<BR><BR>2009-08-19 - Tina H Hamilton - Build Lead review, build incomplete, requires reschedule to October HCG to resolve questions and issues. Plan, HCG 10/21/09 with release 11/24/09<BR><BR>2009-08-20 - Jeremy D Vang - 8/20/09 - PER Dr. Yamaguchi, \"Looks good!  Can we discuss at the domain in two weeks so we can get nursing input before the final version?  Im not sure we have enough detail on how to rewarm if we dont have a device.    I also am not sure about the status of the Arctic Sun or whatever were buying regionally...Gene, do you know? If were going to discuss at the domain, we need to send out at least a week in advance.\"\n\n8/20/09- PER Andrea Thorup, \"I am also working on getting nursing input. So far it looks fairly OK. Janet Margolis used to do this therapy at her old facility and is going to look at it for me early next week.\"<BR><BR>2009-08-21 - Jeremy D Vang - Build base on attached doc and no nursing involvement for suggestion until QA process 8/19/09.<BR><BR>2009-08-25 - Jung M Lee - This order set to be discussed at ICU domain meeting on 9/2 per Kathy Cagney and Dr Yamaguchi.  Reschedule for HCG in october.<BR><BR>2009-08-27 - Jeremy D Vang - 8/26/09 - After lead QA, made minor updates to nursing orders(Notification / Call If), nursing order, and add \"per protoco\" in the comment to RASS order.\n\nSent v5 screen shot to gov for R&C.<BR><BR>2009-08-28 - Jeremy D Vang - \"PER COMMENT, MULTIPLE OCCURRENCES - STAT\" is currently NOT available in for ABG lab.  Currently ALL the start of protocol labs fall under the category of 14 - BLOOD, except for ABG which falls under the category of 170 - RESPIRATORY LAB. The category of 170 does not have Per Comments Multiple Occurrences - STAT available to that category. Adding this frequency to this category would require BAOD approval. Please submit an SR to the Orders BUS group and we can start the process of getting that approved.  Will talk to Sherry when shes back from PTO Tue, 9/1.<BR><BR>2009-09-04 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Purpose and Background added to Description.  Sent for review and comment 9/4/09, due 9/18/09.  Plan for HCG 10/21/09 and release 11/24/09.<BR><BR>2009-09-21 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - This was sent for review and comment prematurely and without the protocol link.  Im sending the comments received from the review and comment period to the domain with an explanation and a request to continue working with the builders for additional changes.  I will send for a second round of review and comment when the order set is ready and with the protocol.  \n<BR><BR>2009-09-22 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Planned HCG date changed to 11/18/09 with release of 12/22/09.<BR><BR>2009-09-23 - Jeremy D Vang - Additional changes after R&C:\n1. Change neuromuscular blockade agents to make cistracurium the primary agent for control of shivering so that demerol, APAP, buspirone and tramadol can be eliminated.\n2. Change all labs to every 6 hours for the first 24 hours, except the daily CBC with diff and Chem 7\n3. Modify the Glucose blood POCT it include \"Confirm all glucoses less than 80 with core lab glucose STAT\"\n4. In Inclusion criteria, change GCS less than 8 to Glascow Coma Scale (GCS) less than 8\n5. Add Exclusion Criteria:  GCS less than or equal to 8\n6. Add an order for the nurse to document the Time the cooling was initiated.\n7.Add an order for the nurse to document a baseline Glasgow Coma Scale\n8.Add an order for the nurse to insert a foley with temperature probe if not already done.\n9.\"CALL IF\" order should mirror hyperlinked protocol:    \n- Call physician if temperature not at target 33°C within 4 hours of cooling initiation.\n- Call physician if temperature less than 87.8°F (31°C) for 30 minutes.\n- Call physician for K+ < 3.2 (goal K+ = 3.5 or greater during cooling).\n- Call physician for magnesium during cooling less than 2 mg/dL (goal magnesium during cooling is 2)\n- Call physician for glucose > 180 and request insulin infusion.\n- Call physician for any unusual or excessive bleeding including melena, hematochezia, hematemesis, or refractory epistaxis.\n- Call physician for shivering not responsive to ordered medications.\n10. Add an order to document the temperature of the cooling device as well as the patients temperature each hour.\n11. Remove versed infusion order and add propofol 40 mcg/kg/min IV by infusion to orders and checklist\n12. Change the every 8 hour labs to every 6 hours (see #2 above)\n13. Add an order for one-time only Chext Xray with reason pre-set to \"s/p cardiac arrest\"\n14. Change exclusion criteria from \"Rususcitation efforts…\" to \"Resuscitation efforts for greater than 30 minutes before return of spontaneous circulation (relative exclusion).\"<BR><BR>2009-10-15 - Jeremy D Vang - 10/15/09 - Made all corrections and send updated screen shot to back to gov.  Andrea Thorup is going to request for  new row to document the the cooling temp.<BR><BR>2009-10-16 - Jung M Lee - Final screen shot and protocol forwarded to HCG.<BR><BR>2009-10-23 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Sent revised order set and protocol for review and comment, due 11/6/09.  Plan for HCG on 11/18/09 and release on 12/22/09.<BR><BR>2009-10-30 - Jeremy D Vang - 10/30/09 - Created 2 tasks: CHG000004200697- Jeremy Vang  /  CHG000004200624 - Orders Team<BR><BR>2009-11-04 - Tina H Hamilton - HME acronym confirmed by Andrea Thorup. Note to Jeremy Vang,  Please spell out the full text for HME on the order set and protocol wherever it appears:\nHeat moisture exchanger (HME)\n<BR><BR>2009-11-06 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - TC from Lorna Yamaguchi to Tina HH:  ED is impacted by this order set and they need to review prior to bring this order set to HCG.  Also, this orderset refers to a \"Temperature Directed Cooling Device\" that not all KP Centers have.  Ambulance companies will start diverting Cardiac Arrest patients to hospitals that have this device so KP Patients may be going to Non-KP hospitals for expensive treatment.  Lorna wants to be sure PCS and Barbara Norrish to be aware of this situation.\n\nEmail to Rob Norris asking him to review, then we will send to ED Domain for review and comment.  Email to K. Cagney explaining situation with Temp. Directed Cooling Device and asking her to work with PCS to be sure they are aware of this.  \n\nPlanned HCG date changed to 12/16/09 and planned release date moved to 1/26/10.<BR><BR>2009-11-10 - Tina H Hamilton - Rob Norris responded to initial review of screen shots with recommendations for changes. Lorna Yamaguchi indicates that she is awaiting ICU input and will then send changes. Changes to be made before this is sent for review and comment.<BR><BR>2009-11-16 - Tina H Hamilton - ED respondent, Rob Norris and Greg Marelich exchanging comments. A text extraction from the draft KPHC build was sent to ICU sponsors with a request that they edit this document to clarify for builders exactly what changes are desired. If received by 11/18, will make every effort to send for review and comment in prep for 12/16 HCG.<BR><BR>2009-11-17 - Tina H Hamilton - ED comments added to text/word file i