rning; 1) portable CXR in am, \"f/u cardiac arrest\" (if you can preload comments into Radiology orders) and 2) EKG in am.\n-Can you add to the Users & Departments affected, \"Emergency Dept Physicians\"? I think our decision was to include, \"ED\" in the synonyms.<BR><BR>2009-12-03 - Jeremy D Vang - 12/3/09 - updated per Dr. Marelich request and sent screen shot v10.\n\nI am in my Critical Care Domain mtg right now, and the group has made two additional requests:\nfor the Measure Temperature order, change, \"If patient is anuric...\" to \"If patient is anuric, use alternate continuous core temperature monitoring.\"\nfor the abbreviation of \"TOF\" please spell it out instead: \"train of four\"<BR><BR>2009-12-03 - Jeremy D Vang - 12/3/09 - New SR created for \"Change EDP order Speech Therapy [45] order config (OCC) to look like Physical Therapy [42].  Add \"Questions\" to (OCC) for ONLY at the orderset level.\"  Emailed Adam and cc Trevor for IA.<BR><BR>2009-12-07 - Jeremy D Vang - 12/4/09 - Per Dr. Yamaguchi, \" The ICU Regional Chiefs and managers  meeting is on 12/10.  Ill also show the screen shots and distribute  paper version of the orderset that will be presented at HCG on 12/16 so the facilities can begin planning implementation.  This is probably the most complicated orderset weve attempted since it spans 36 hours. \nEGDT is only 6 hours.   i want the facilities to have as much lead time as possible.  Even if the HCG does not approve, the substance of the orderset will hopefully remain intact with only minor content changes requested.\"\n12/4/09 - \" Whoops - one more thing to add - can you put back the open bullets in the lab section to help the nurses with the handoff?\"\n12/03/09 - Per Dr. Marelich, \"In the Measure Temperature order again, please remove the phrase contained by the parentheses - \"(e.g. Rectal probe)\" Sorry that wasnt clear, I should have typed the whole thing out. The request at the domain was to remove mention of rectal probes altoget