NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-22 05:02:00','2009-08-06 02:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SRO KPHC IP ADULT- CRRT Heparin\n\nPurpose/intent of order set change: \n   The purpose for this request is for the KPHC order set for Heparin CRRT to match our current paper order set and our practice at Santa Rosa. \n1)    In the medication section, Heparin, please add below option to bolus for a low PTT result; this allows the MD greater flexibility for a low PTT. \n\" Bolus with xxx units and increase administration rate by 200units per hour.\"  \n\n2)   Secondly, in the medication section, Heparin, please add below option for a lower concentration of Heparin.  We would recommend two concentrations of Heparin in the syringe for the pump:  High Dose Heparin Concentration (which is currently in this order set) and Low Dose Heparin Concentration.\n\n  \"Lower Dose Continuous Heparin Infusion,  2,000units in 20mL, 100units/mL\" (the nurses prefer the lower dose).  \n\n\nBackground information/context setting:  For both of these requests, this is our current order set and our practice. \n1)   If the PTT is low and takes time to get to a therapeutic range,  we risk clotting the filter.  A bolus gives the MD more flexibility to treat this result. \n2)   We absolutely need to have two different heparin concentrations, for the times we have the drip running at <1000 units per hour.  The only option in this order set currently is 20,000units in 20mL or 1,000units per mL.  For patients receiving less than 1000units per hour, or .5mL per hour, we can not be assured that such a small volume is infusing properly.  Again, the risk is clotting the filter.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-28 - Sherry Ellis - Reviewed by TIGR team.  SRO requested.  Need Domain lead approval and suit approval.<BR><BR>2009-04-28 - Sherry Ellis - Assigned to G. Gaskins for appropriate approvals, then will be assigned to M. Nguyen.<BR><BR>2009-05-04 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Emailed Vijay Rathore for approval to proceed.  Requested response by 5/11/09.<BR><BR>2009-06-02 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Second request sent to Dr. Rathore for approval to build.<BR><BR>2009-06-19 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - New request sent to Dr. Rathore for approval to proceed.<BR><BR>2009-07-07 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - email from Vijay Rathore:\nPlease proceed with the requested changes on CRRT order set (SR 3576522)\n#1 Under the medication section add an additional order (single select not pre checked)\nHeparin Bolus  Administer heparin *** units intravenous bolus because of sub therapeutic PTT and increase rate by 200 units per hour. \n#2 under medication section heparin iv continuous built a choice for lower concentration of heparin 2000 units in 20 mls, with same administration instructions.\n\nthe question I have for the requestors are they going to use anti-Xa levels to titrate heparin ?\n\n   The purpose for this request is for the KPHC order set for Heparin CRRT to match our current paper order set and our practice at Santa Rosa. \n1)    In the medication section, Heparin, please add below option to bolus for a low PTT result; this allows the MD greater flexibility for a low PTT. \n\" Bolus with xxx units and increase administration rate by 200units per hour.\"  \n\n2)   Secondly, in the medication section, Heparin, please add below option for a lower concentration of Heparin.  We would recommend two concentrati