s/Procedures User wants someone to come by and discuss modification of a new order set for the ped. surgeons.\n\n11/4/09\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change:\n<specific purpose for use of new order set, details of changes being proposed>\nThis is a Post Op HAS ASC Order Set designed for Pediatrics.  Currently none exists specifically for children.\n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\n<as provided by sponsor>\nOrders for children are more complicated than adults since they are weight based.  These orders are more time consuming and prone to error if not standardized.  \nThis order set will improve Peri-Op efficiency in several ways:\n1. By decreasing the time surgeons spend on discharge orders, case turnover will be improved.\n2. By standardizing discharge meds and doses, they will get to the discharge pharmacy more reliably and with less errors requiring pharmacy call backs and patients will be discharged sooner without delays.\n3. By increasing patient safety with standardized orders reviewed by pharmacy committees.\n\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\n<Thomas Curran, Pediatric Surgery>\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\n<Pediatric Surgery SUIT, PeriOp Domain>',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-30 - Terrance L Tirado - Once assigned, please contact me and I will send you email with screenshots of each med order for this Order Set<BR><BR>2009-05-05 - Terrance L Tirado - Per Margaret (Maggie) Mentakis, this enhancement request is approved by his peer group.\nThere are only 3 pediatric surgeons in the region, and they all agree.  That counts.\n<BR><BR>2009-05-05 - Terrance L Tirado - check progress with sherry j ellis or tina herman hamilton they deal with order sets\n\n\n<BR><BR>2009-05-12 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, this requires agreement and process with AMB team to build meds. Meeting pending.<BR><BR>2009-07-09 - Tina H Hamilton - 7/9/09: Per Bill Yee, more info 7/13 re: build assignment.<BR><BR>2009-07-14 - Tina H Hamilton - Per Minh review, sent to Maggie Mentakis for perspective on new orderset vs adding DC med section to current post op order set.<BR><BR>2009-07-21 - Tina H Hamilton - Per Maggie Mentakis, adding ambulatory meds to existing order set. Changed status to Pending resource assignment, owner Ming Nguyen<BR><BR>2009-07-23 - Tina H Hamilton - Thomas curran confirmed via email that this is for a new order set. Screen shots provided within email, see attachment.\nActually, it would be best if we created a new order set patterned after: \nPost Op HAS ASC [414410] -> I would title it as: Post Op HAS ASC PED\n (Similar to what we did with Day of Surgery and Intra Op Orders PED)\nIt would not make sense to add this to our admit orders, it is primarily for HAS discharges.\nSorry if there was confusion about this.<BR><BR>2009-08-11 - Tina H Hamilton - Minh Nguyen to plan build, for 10/21/09 HCG, Release 11/24/09. Content and build finalization to be coordinated by build and pharmacy team in sync with milestone prod dates. \nNote, order set name will change from HAS ASC to Outpatient Surgery.<BR><BR>2009-08-13 - Minh X Nguyen - Sent screenshot for sponsor review<BR><BR>2009-08-21 - Minh X Nguyen - Screenshots being review by Dr. Curran.  Dr. Curran is reviewing this with his peers. There is discussion of adding non-med orders, so well need an AC assigned as 2nd owner.<BR><BR>2009-08-25 - Tina H Hamilton - Additional post op orders added. \nHi Minh-\n    This is looking pretty good.  I think we are closing in on what we want added.  There are a few more things still:\n\n1. I agree with Dr. Mentakis that there should be a discharge order.  I cant remember if that is popping up automatically from the navigator when we use this on a real patient.\n2. Do the weight based orders automatically insert patient friendly sig instructions?\n3. I would like to also add:\n    a.) Septra (generic OK) 40/200/5 ml, dose 20mg/kg/d divided BID.\n    b.) Norco 5/325, dose 1-2 tabs every 4-6 hours as needed for severe pain\n4. Other PACU orders to consider, but I understand may take longer to implement:\n      a.) Toot Sweet - may give prn fussiness (this is a supply room item, not Pyxis).\n      b.)  Portable CXR\n      c.)   CBC w diff\n      d.)   Chem 7\n      e.)   PT, PTT\nemail forwarded to Sean Ryan to complete non-med build.<BR><BR>2009-08-25 - Minh X Nguyen - sent email to the group asking to send addition request.  included Sean Ryan as non-med builder.<BR><BR>2009-08-25 - Tina H Hamilton - Dr DuBois agrees to move forward with changes as presented by Dr. Curran. Plan, for review and comment 9/14, to HCG 10/21/09 and release 11/24/09. Willl need to be to QA lead 9/9/09<BR><BR>2009-08-28 - Minh X Nguyen - Med build completed per latest email from Dr. Curran.  Sent email alert to Sean Ryan.<BR><BR>2009-09-10 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Changes planned HCG date to 11/18/09.  This will not be ready by the deadline for October HCG, content still with sponsor.<BR><BR>2009-10-05 - Minh X Nguyen - Dr. Curran is showing the screenshots to his local domain.  Not sure if he understand approval process.  Recommend that Governance contact him.<BR><BR>2009-11-03 - Minh X Nguyen - Tina to work with Dr. Mentakis to bring to Periop domain for approval.<BR><BR>2009-11-03 - Tina H Hamilton - Inquiry from Maggie Mentakis as to status. Sent email to Maggie and Jason Londeree describing governance steps (SUIT approval, domain OK to circulate for review and comment, public scrutiny, HCG, Med Exec notification, release).\n\nForwarded last email (9/23) with screen shots awaiting Dr. Currans OK to Maggie, Dr. Londeree and Dr. Curran with note:\nIf this has been approved by the pedi surgery colleagues, please let us know; if approved by Maggie and Marla, well send out for public scrutiny (review and comment). This would take 2 weeks, so this would go to the 12/16 HCG and then get released the 4th Wed in January.<BR><BR>2009-11-03 - Tina H Hamilton - Approved by Maggie Mentakis. Per Thomas Curran, Maggie has a good point.\nIt applies to both LABS and STUDIES.I would like to add to the blue header:\nLABS - TO BE DONE IN PACU\nSTUDIES - TO BE DONE IN PACU\n\nAlso, I just noticed that the weight-based Infant Tylenol is 12 mg/kg/dose and the Childrens Tylenol is 15 mg/kg/dose.\nI would use 15 mg/kg/dose for both of these.\nNote to Minh to complete changes then send to gov team for review and comment.<BR><BR>2009-11-03 - Tina H Hamilton - Requested background and context from Thomas Curran<BR><BR>2009-11-04 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - The name of this order set is being changed to Pediatric Outpatient Surgery per compliance request to remove HAS and ASC from names.<BR><BR>2009-11-04 - Tina H Hamilton - received background and context from Thomas Curran;  added to description.<BR><BR>2009-11-05 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Sent for review and comment, due 11/19/09<BR><BR>2009-11-23 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Comments collated and sent to Drs. Mentakis and Curran due 12/1/09.<BR><BR>',1287,1288,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2572,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Mark Rudow','',3613771,NULL,'OS Revision ANES Adult PACU Brief',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',NULL,'0','L','R','M','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','ANS','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','PERI','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-01 00:00:00','2009-06-19 00:00:00','2009-06-19 00:00:00','2009-06-23 12:20:40','2009-05-05 13:22:06',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',967,NULL,201,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-05 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','190