jor adverse cardiac events after PCI. Since nearly all patients require aspirin and clopidogrel after PCI, the option to order omeprazole via this order set is being removed. For patients who require treatment of peptic ulcer disease, H2 blocker is the preferred agent. 2. There is a \"hard stop\" for ordering aspirin (or identifying a contraindication) in this order set. However, aspirin may be ordered outside this order set (e.g. PTA medication). That option has now been included. \nPhysician Sponsor Name: Dr. Philip C Lee \nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content: Cardiology domain lead for inpt HC',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2591,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3643008,NULL,'DO NOT REOPEN THIS   (SR) MCH-Perinatal-OS Oxytocin/IVF Ordersets',NULL,'OS',NULL,'0',NULL,'0','H','0','H','0','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','H','N','N',' ',NULL,'AR','N','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','2009-06-12 15:33:08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-18 08:36:41','2009-05-13 15:37:30',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',687,NULL,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-14 08:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DO NOT REOPEN THIS   (SR) MCH - Perinatal - OS Oxytocin/IVF Orderset.\nPharmacy