es) has been added.  Same comments for both questions 1 and 2 below.  List me as the sponsor and the Ortho SUIT as the approving entity.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-10 - Tina H Hamilton - email John Woll:\nI would have no objection to changing each section to radio buttons.\n\nHowever, if we are to change the order set, I would suggest updating  \nthe entire analgesic portion of the order set to allow for the maximum  \ndose based on weight and tylenol components and make sure we have  \noptions for weight based dosing that by default give the maximum dose  \n(based on the tylenol dose) for a given patient, as well as offer  \ntablet options for both the tylenol and vicodin.\n\nAs it stands now, I enter the analgesics by completion matching to  \nensure that the child is getting maximal relief.  for example (all  \ndoses listed below can be given q 4h):\n\ntylenol 15 mg/kg per dose given q4h\ntyco elixir (12-120) /5 ml = 0.625 mg/kg q4\nvicodin elixir (2.5-166)/ 5 ml = 0.452 mg/kg q4\n\nIn addition to these analgesics, we should probably also add valium  \n(both elixir and tablet) to be used prn muscle spasm at 0.1 mg/kg q8\n\nThese changes would be a big help towards updating and improving this  \norder set.\n\nThe two remaining that we need to update are this and the upper  \nextremity order set.<BR><BR>2009-06-10 - Tina H Hamilton - note to Dr. Woll; Upper Extremity Pain modules were updated 1/28/09 per standard ortho smart groups.<BR><BR>2009-06-23 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, noted SR missing owner, added Thomas Chun, pending resource assignment.<BR><BR>2009-11-04 - Thomas Chun - new screens done.<BR><BR>2009-11-17 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Background and purpose added to description.  Planned HCG changed to 12/16/09 and release changed to 1/26/10.  Sent for review and comment, due 12/1/09.<BR><BR>2009-12-03 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Change from review and comment:\nAdd Norco 5/325 one po q3h between the elixir and vicodin in the moderate pain section.\nThe