parate \"do not give orders\"; defaults as noted below)\nOrder # 1Do not give after spinal injection or epidural insertion (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n    Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) 1 mg/kg (or higher) QD dosing OR any BID dosing until at least 24 hours after spinal injection. \n    Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) 40 mg QD until at least 8 hours after spinal injection.\n    Do not give fondaparinux (Arixtra) until at least 24 hours after spinal injection.\n\nOrder #2 Do not give if epidural catheter is in place (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n     Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox), IV unfractionated heparin, fondaparinux  (Arixtra), clopidogrel (Plavix) or ticlodipine (Ticlid) while an epidural catheter is in place. \n     If warfarin is ordered on patient with an epidural catheter in place, notify anesthesia.\n     SQ heparin is permissible when an epidural catheter is in place. TID dosing should be used with caution since there is no data supporting its use. (added 8/18/09)\n\nOrder #3 Do not give after removal of epidural catheter (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n     Do not give SQ or IV heparin until at least one hour after removal of epidural catheter. \n     Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) until at least 2 hours after removal of epidural catheter.    \n     Do not give fondaparinux (Arixtra) until at least 12 hours after removal of epidural catheter.\n\n\nDefaults:\nANES WARD-ICU EPIDURAL/ SPINAL SINGLE DOSE NARCOTIC',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-21 - Tina H Hamilton - The TIGR team reviewed the following SR.\nReferred back to Mark Rudow and Susan Muha for clarification of build and BPA.<BR><BR>2009-07-23 - Tina H Hamilton - discussed requirements with Mark Rudow and updated<BR><BR>2009-07-28 - Sherry Ellis - Discussed revised description of ticket for BPAs requests.  Ticket will be re-directed to Orders Bus queue for ACs to evaluate technical feasibility of request