iew \"If unable to void within 30 minutes, straight cath to obtain specimen\"\n\nThis applies to all POCT testing on ED ordersets (Pregnancy, UA, specific gravity, etc.)\nRefer to extract attachment.\nSeparate SR 3949367 for preference list changes.\n\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change: To allow nursing staff to obtain urine via a straight cath\nspecimen if patient is unable to void\n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change: Obtaining a urine sample is often the\n\"rate-limiting-step\" in the evaluation of an ED patient , particularly in female patients of childbearing\nage with any number of complaints . There can be significant delays in ED flow when a urine sample\nhas not been obtained for a urinalysis or urine pregnancy test . This has a ripple effect through the\nrest of the ED, resulting in the patient occupying the bed longer than they otherwise would ,\npotentially delaying care of patients in the waiting room . By enabling and empowering our RN s to\nobtain a straight cath specimen , we hope to reduce delays in the ER and improve our efficiency .\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name: Robert Norris, MD; South Sacramento and Regional KPHC , Emergency\nMedicine\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content: ED',NULL,'1210022870ï££I591970ï££Daria L Rosen\n\nPer Ryan Lambert - Clincon owns ordersetsï£¢',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2700,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3901472,NULL,'(SR) Order - Diet - Add new verbiage to Comments section of Advance as Tolerated.',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERS TECH','IPORDTEC','End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient Orders/Procedures','Order Detail Configuration','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-09-09 11:58:01','2009-09-09 13:00:00','2009-11-02 09:20:22','2009-11-02 11:40:45','2009-07-30 16:39:16',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1363,NULL,95,NUL