tails. Related to SR 3849861\n\nSusan Muha, SSS\n707-292-4866',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-08-12 - Tina H Hamilton - Stephanie Gavigan has met with Drs Rudow and Mentakis regarding this BPA. Requires further investigation. Based upon Tina HH email 8/12/09, the following details and questions are added for discussion.\n\nDr. Rudow suggests that the BPA display generic text (group needs to define): \nFor example, \"This patient has had a spinal/epidural insertion and anticoagulants may be contraindicated. <Display the details of the spinal/epidural timing order indicating date/time and meds/dose if entered>. Please refer to this link to review exclusion criteria prior to ordering or administering anticoagulants.\"\nThe BPA is generic\nThe time/date and med/dose details of the \"spinal/epidural\" timing order are shown (is it possible to extract details from the order into the BPA?)\nContains a link to a document that provides the exclusion criteria as shown in orders #1, #2 and #3 (is it possible to insert a link into a BPA?)\n\nRefer to SR 3849861 for text imbedded in each of the \"do not give orders\". (Will there be 3 links or 1?)\n\nWhat are the criteria for the BPA?\nThe spinal/epidural timing order has been entered\nThe \"do not give\" order(s) have been entered\n\nWhat is the trigger for the BPA?\nNursing will see the BPA when; attempting to administer anticoagulants from the MAR. The BPA would not be specific to particular drugs or doses, but class \"anticoagulants\" (see drug list included in current BPA, needs to be verified)\nPharmacy will see the BPA when: verifying anticoagulant medication orders, class \"anticoagulants\" (see drug list included in current BPA, needs to be verified)\nPhysician will see the BPA when: entering/signing anticoagulant orders, class \"anticoagulants\" (see drug list included in current BPA, needs to be verified)\n\nNote, the DO NOT GIVE orders will appear on the PER\n\nWhat turns the BPA off?\nThe Anesthesiologists will need to DC the \"do not give\" orders when rounding. Until the anesthesiologist DCs the order, it will continue to fire upon the triggering events above.\nDownside: when all 3 \"do not give\" orders are defaulted, the ANES will need to DC all 3 to turn the BPA off\nUpside: information from all of the BPAs is available\nIt does not appear that it will be possible to logically time the BPAs to fire during a specific time period since the timing varies depending upon type of procedure and medication dose/frequency ordered.\n\nWill the current BPA for \"do not give, epidural catheter\" continue to fire in addition to the ANES BPAs?<BR><BR>2009-08-12 - Tina H Hamilton - Reassiged to ORDERS BUS, note to Sherry Ellis, Stephanie Gavigan, Thomas Chun and Minh Nguyen (cc Mark Rudow and Maggie Mentakis) with details of above note.<BR><BR>2009-08-24 - Adam Huffman - Initial Approval: Adam J Huffman<BR><BR>2009-10-20 - Stephanie M Gavigan - WITS Build is in Progress. Pending a request for 3 new EAPs that will trigger these BPAs. Moving Planned End Date.<BR><BR>2009-11-11 - Stephanie M Gavigan - Working with Minh on BPA with the 3 new EAPs (see related SR) - Moving planned end date out to account for more build time and testing.<BR><BR>2009-12-08 - Stephanie M Gavigan - Meetings scheduled in January to bring in all necessary teams and gather all new requirements, while allowing information gathering time to determine what the system will allow.<BR><BR>',834,1040,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2713,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3933608,NULL,'KPH CIP SRO- Change med frequency',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','R','M','D','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','PERI','PERN','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-27 11:05:39','2009-10-28 00:01:00','2009-11-02 11:40:53','2009-08-10 16:01:02',' ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',96