00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-18 10:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EAP, 3 new for Do Not Give Anticoagulant orders\n\nPharmacy Monitoring orders / Nursing orders (3 separate \"do not give orders\"; defaults as noted below)\nOrder # 1Do not give after spinal injection or epidural insertion (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n    Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) 1 mg/kg (or higher) QD dosing OR any BID dosing until at least 24 hours after spinal injection. \n    Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) 40 mg QD until at least 8 hours after spinal injection.\n    Do not give fondaparinux (Arixtra) until at least 24 hours after spinal injection.\n\nOrder #2 Do not give if epidural catheter is in place (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n     Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox), IV unfractionated heparin, fondaparinux  (Arixtra), clopidogrel (Plavix) or ticlodipine (Ticlid) while an epidural catheter is in place. \n     If warfarin is ordered on patient with an epidural catheter in place, notify anesthesia.\n     SQ heparin is permissible when an epidural catheter is in place. TID dosing should be used with caution since there is no data supporting its use.\n\nOrder #3 Do not give after removal of epidural catheter (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n     Do not give SQ or IV heparin until at least one hour after removal of epidural catheter. \n     Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) until at least 2 hours after removal of epidural catheter.    \n     Do not give fondaparinux (Arixtra) until at least 12 hours after removal of epidural catheter.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-08-12 - Tina H Hamilton - Replace the \"do not give anticoagulant order\" in the following three four ordersets. Stephanie Gavigan is involved in this project. Create 3 new orders\n\nAnes Ward - ICU Epidural Continuous Long Acting Narcotic   [415426]\nANES WARD-ICU EPIDURAL/ SPINAL SINGLE DOSE NARCOTIC   [414542]\nANES Ward/ICU Epidural Continuous Local Anesthetic  [414539]\nANES OB Labor Epidural Order Set (414540] added 7/28/09 per Mark Rudow\n\nCreated TASK related to SR 3849861\n\n\nPharmacy Monitoring orders / Nursing orders (3 separate \"do not give orders\"; defaults as noted below)\nOrder # 1Do not give after spinal injection or epidural insertion (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n    Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) 1 mg/kg (or higher) QD dosing OR any BID dosing until at least 24 hours after spinal injection. \n    Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) 40 mg QD until at least 8 hours after spinal injection.\n    Do not give fondaparinux (Arixtra) until at least 24 hours after spinal injection.\n\nOrder #2 Do not give if epidural catheter is in place (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n     Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox), IV unfractionated heparin, fondaparinux  (Arixtra), clopidogrel (Plavix) or ticlodipine (Ticlid) while an epidural catheter is in place. \n     If warfarin is ordered on patient with an epidural catheter in place, notify anesthesia.\n     SQ heparin is permissible when an epidural catheter is in place.\n\nOrder #3 Do not give after removal of epidural catheter (BPA to fire with specific language relative to this order)\n     Do not give SQ or IV heparin until at least one hour after removal of epidural catheter. \n     Do not give enoxaparin (Lovenox) until at least 2 hours after removal of epidural catheter.    \n     Do not give fondaparinux (Arixtra) until at least 12 hours after removal of epidural catheter.\n<BR><BR>2009-08-17 - Tina H Hamilton - Per mail Mark Rudow:\nId like to add a sentence to the Do not giive while epidural catheter in place order - Next to the SQ heparin section add \"TID dosing is not recommended\".<BR><BR>2009-08-18 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, Sherry Ellis sent follow up note to Adam Huffman requesting owner assignment.<BR><BR>2009-08-18 - Tina H Hamilton - Per Mark Rudow ema