to Production in July.  We will have to keep the SR open until we are able to add a working link in the smartlist of the discharge summary note.\n\n(By the way, we fixed the spelling error.)\n?1215123964?D899443?Alexander H Koppel\n\nIll speak with Brian and see if we can work with the new ED DC meds link.?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2742,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3984023,NULL,'KPHC low and high intensive insulin order sets, simplify the admin instruction in the hypoglycemia protocol orders',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','R','H','D','intensive insulin',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Wor','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','MEDSURG','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2010-01-20 09:05:09','2010-02-23 09:28:42',NULL,'2009-12-22 12:06:35','2009-08-25 15:11:53',' ','',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','',981,NULL,95,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-25 03:20:00','2009-09-15 02:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KPHC low and high intensive insulin order sets, simplify the admin instruction in the hypoglycemia protocol orders.  Current orders re-stated the dosing information in the admin instruction that is already captured on the protocol.  Simplify these orders to simply refer to the protocols.\n\nPurpose/intent of new order set or change:\nTo simplify D50 orders for treatment of hypoglycemia in Intensive Insulin Therapy order sets\n\nBackground information/context setting, rationale for change:\n        D50 orders contain excessive amount of information that are already included in the respective hypoglycemia protocols.\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nGreg Marelich, MD, SSC, Pulmonary & Critical Care Medicine\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\nCritical Care',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-08-25 - Minh X Nguyen - Comment from Kathy Cagney:  I agree as well, it keeps the MAR cleaner.  I would confirm with nursing staff that they are actually referencing the hyperlinked protocol before changing it though.  What would be needed to make that change?\n\nso need to confirm with RN leads (Lisa Rohr/Ashley Randall group) before proceeding with change.<BR><BR>2009-09-01 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, reviewed protocol and the current admin instructions in the hypoglycemia orders. Plan, Minh to mock up change communication and send to Lorna Yamaguchi and Kathy Cagney for approval by 9/15. This is a medium level change, plan for 10/27 release.<BR><BR>2009-09-14 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Changes sent to Greg Marelich and Kathy Cagney by Minh on 9/10/09.  Response from Dr. Marelich:\nMinh, the changes with the administration language in the D50W orders is ok. Ive filled in the other requested details for this change, below.\n\nNot to complicate things, but another matter has come up with these order sets (and the sliding scale insulin order sets, for that matter).\nIts the issue about the recognized positive bias (up to 40% in some samples) with fingerstick glucose readings from the point-of-care monitors, which we discussed at our ICU Directors-Mgrs meeting on 9/10. Because One Touch meters tend to read high in anemia - which could lead to unappreciated hypoglycemia - clinical experts from Endocrinology and Critical Care will soon recommend that patients on insulin or medications that can significantly lower glucose (insulin secretagogues such as glipizide) have One Touch  glucose meter results of < 80 mg/dL retested. Special patients at risk for hypoglycemia with fingerstick glucoses <80 are those unable to call for help when symptomatic, such as the very young, those with dementia, and those with altered levels of consciousness. \n\nThis is considerably different than our current hypoglycemia treatment threshold of \"less than 60\" on the Intensive Insulin order sets\n\nCurrently, our protocols state, \"Obtain serum glucose to confirm finger stick blood glucose greater than 500 mg/dL. \"\nWe could change this to read, \"Obtain serum glucose to confirm finger stick blood glucose greater than 500 mg/dL OR finger stick blood glucose less than 80 mg/dL with altered level of consciousness or dementia..\" This should be done for both low- and hi-dose intensive insulin protocols. \n\n(I dont think any of the pediatricians are using these protocols, thus Im not mentioning \"the very young\" in the proposed change language for these orders.)\n\nThis is somethiing of a patient safety issue, and it might certainly warrant action sooner than 10/27.\nWe might want to include similar changes to the other insulin order sets.\n\nSorry, thought Id bring this up at the same time.\n\n\nReply from Herb Szeto to Rick Dlott:\nRick,\n\nThe simplest thing for the med-surg ordersets would be to embed the serum test into the hypoglycemic  protocol which currently triggers at a glucose of 70.    Should we move the treatment threshold to 80 as well if we use 80 as the threshold for further testing?\n\nPurpose and background added to description.\n\n<BR><BR>2009-09-15 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Hello All, \nIf you want to go ahead with this change, this turns into a high level of governance requiring HCG approval.  Also the protocols need to updated as well.  Please clearly indicate the changes you want on the protocols which are attached.  Alternatively, you could make the D50 change and submit a separate SR to change the protocol.  Please advise on how you would like to proceed.<BR><BR>2009-09-29 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Plan for HCG on 11/18/09 and release on 12/22/09.<BR><BR>2009-11-20 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Planned HCG changed to 1/20/10, no response from sponsor.<BR><BR>',981,981,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2743,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Elliot Morrison','',3987696,NULL,'(SR) MCH-PERINATAL-OS: Vital Signs Weblink - Antepartum',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','R','H','D','vital signs antepartum',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Sch','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','PERN','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-11-18 15:38:00','2009-12-22 15:39:00',NULL,'2009-12-22 12:06:36','2009-08-26 13:24:59',' ','',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','',1232,NULL,95,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-11-18 00:00:00','2009-10-21 00:00:00','2009-10-21 00:00:00','2009-11-04 00:00:00','2009-11-05 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-11-09 00:00:00','2009-11-05 00:00:00','2009-11-11 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-11-23 00:00:00','2009-11-20 00:00:00','2009-11-25 00:00:00','2009-11-25 00:00:00','2009-11-25 00:00:00','2009-11-25 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-26 01:38:00','2009-11-25 08:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'(SR) MCH-PERINATAL-OS: Vital Signs Weblink 