us, and Levemir so it is less confusing.\n_____________________\nHerbert Szeto, MD, MPH\n\nMinh,\nI agree with adding it but I do not think it should replace Lantus.\n\nPamela Kershner, M.D.\n\nMinh Nguyen/CA/KAIPERM\nHello Drs. Kershner and Szeto,\n\nThe DUM (Drug Use Management) group is requesting to have Levemir added to the Diabetes Mellitus Order Set.  \n\nJocelyn K Chan/CA/KAIPERM \n09/09/2009 03:39 PM\nHi Minh,\n\nIm not sure when the Diabetes Mellitus order set is up for review.  But I was wondering if I can put in a request for possible modification.  As I mentioned before, Drug Use Management is working on an initiative focusing on the preferential use of NPH insulin first for Type 2 diabetics.  In addition to Lantus, Levemir (insulin detemir) is another long-acting insulin analog that is available.  Its still more costly than NPH but its slightly cheaper than Lantus.  Levemir has been positioned as an alternative to NPH for Type 2 diabetics who experience significant hypoglycemia on NPH.  This order set appears to be focused on Type 2 diabetics so I was wondering if the physician lead and/or decision support group would consider adding Levemir as an option in the order set.<BR><BR>2009-09-22 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, high level change, adding new med choice. Will work with Dr Szeto to finalize screen shots.<BR><BR>',981,981,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2773,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Mark Rudow','',4049715,NULL,'OS Rev; Cataract Day of Surgery, Change CRNA authorization verbiage',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','R','L','D','CRNA',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','ANS','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','PERI','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-29 16:01:01','2009-09-30 09:28:31','2009-09-15 12:51:05',' ','',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','',1232,NULL,201,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-22 00:00:00','1900-01