uideline (based on the current medical literature), with emphasis on how these changes are translated to HC order set revisions. Relevant changes have been reviewed by QOS to ensure compliance with TJC core measures.\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nPhilip C Lee, MD\nCo-Chair of  KPNC ACS Guideline Team\nCardiology Domain Lead\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\nACS Guideline Team\nCardiology SUIT\nMed Surg and ED Domains',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-10-06 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, HIGH level change. For domain approval.<BR><BR>2009-10-06 - Tina H Hamilton - Sent note to Anne Chang referencing the changes to the beta blocker requirement and extra buttons for no absolute or relative contraindications. Pending response.<BR><BR>2009-10-06 - Tina H Hamilton - Sent email to domain leads (Herb Szeto and Rob Norris) for approval to build. Also asking Phil Lee for background and context for changes.<BR><BR>2009-10-06 - Tina H Hamilton - Various responses to change document. Note to Phil Lee to update build document as needed based upon comments from Herb Szeto and Jane Humphreys\nJane Humphreys: Thank you so much for checking with us about the Beta Blocker build!  I followed up with Dr. Szeto, and we do not want to remove the hardstop to order or document contraindication to Beta Blocker.  Please see Herbs comments below.  \nThanks again for connecting with us!\nJane\n\nSorry- further clarification around the b-blocker issue,  I think that it would be better to keep the section as required along with the updated warning for hypotension/shock.  If patients do not get started on B-blockers at admission or we dont document a contriaindication, there is significant risk that this will result in a core measure fallout for B-blocker at discharge.  There is no other way to reliably remind the provider to start a b-blocker prior to discharge other than the discharge instruction link that is not used consistently.  I hope that removing the IV metoprolol from the section would minimize the risk of complications.\n\nAnne Chang states that Rob Norris was to submit additional reasons for lytic delay, due 10/1. Note to Rob Norris inquiring as to status. \n<BR><BR>2009-10-20 - Tina H Hamilton - Discussed with Rob Norris who has agreed to submit build documents per agreements with Herb Szeto and Phil Lee.<BR><BR>2009-11-03 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, build document received from Rob Norris.<BR><BR>2009-11-03 - Tina H Hamilton - Removed original attachment to avoid confusion.  Pharmacy primary owner; assign to Emily Foo pending resource assignment. \n<BR><BR>2009-12-04 - Emily C Foo - Build started, question for enoxaparin dosing based on new guidelines sent to Dr. Norris who will contact Drs. Phil Lee and Herb Szeto to determine whether changes are needed plus need to consider removal of the maintenance dose after 1st 2 doses.<BR><BR>2009-12-15 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR discussion, per Emily Foo, Rob Norris sent her a new build document on 12/8. Next steps, to build and then obtain domain approval. Weblink is pending, need reference document from Dr. Lee. \nRob Norris and Phil Lee to validate weblink. \nFor 1/20/10 HCG, all build documents and references to be done and ready for review and comment by Friday, 12/18. Emily Foo to follow up with Drs. Norris and Lee to ascertain this. \nTentative plans for 1/20/10 HCG and 2/23/10 release if above schedule met.<BR><BR>2009-12-21 - Emily C Foo - New revised build document provided by Dr. Norris.<BR><BR>',1313,1041,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2785,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Phil Lee','',4100460,NULL,'OS ED HBS Rev Integrilin 414176, see attachment',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','R','H','S','Integrilin',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Pen','CARD','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','Requester Information','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','MEDSURG','ED','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-