H Hamilton - Tina H Hamilton\n\n5/27/08 TIGR review and discussion with B Hoberman: will require PRL and changes to PER for orders. In queue for build, R&D<BR><BR>2008-10-28 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - TIGR Review, assign to Mark Knoblach per B. Hoberman.<BR><BR>2009-02-25 - Mark A Knoblauch - Maureen Alano has compliled and compared all wound care order sets from around the region with input from HBS, RCST, and wound care nurses.  Meeting scheduled this week to review and move foward with build.<BR><BR>2009-03-17 - Mark A Knoblauch - Comparisons complete of paper order sets.  iNGG workgroups re pressure ulcers currently revising flowsheets / documentation standards.  I am involved in those groups.  will assemble findings and begin work on order set.<BR><BR>2009-06-19 - Mark A Knoblauch - Still waiting for wound workgroups to be finished with changes to nursing documentation.<BR><BR>2009-07-31 - Tina H Hamilton - Mark Knoblauch, SR handoff email: Sherry Ellis will be build team contact, pending content finalization and protocols per wound care groups.<BR><BR>2009-10-21 - Sherry Ellis - Email from Dr. Szeto inquiring about the progress of this SR, replied and cced Ann OBrien stating I have not heard anything from the workgroups.<BR><BR>2009-10-27 - Sherry Ellis - Spoke with Andrea Thorup about this orderset request.  She will work with regional pressure ulcer workgroups to develop an orderset build template.  When content is agreed she will submit to orderset group with comprehensive build documentation,<BR><BR>2009-11-16 - Deltese L Duncan - NCC SR Review Meeting 11.09.09:\nUpdated next status check with the planned end date.\n\nEmail sent to Andrea T. requesting the status of this request.<BR><BR>',984,974,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2816,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3359095,NULL,'OS Multiple - PT/INR Reconfigure: INR: On warfarin, INR: No warfarin therapy',NULL,'SR',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Wor','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-22 12:06:56','2009-02-11 12:57:52',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',959,NULL,313,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-28 09:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OS Multiple - PT/INR Reconfigure: INR: On warfarin, INR: No warfarin therapy\n\nApproved by HCG 12.17.09 based upon review of revised CVA/TIA Initial Evaluation orderset. This will relieve the need for a hard stop in orders. \n\nPer Herb Szeto\nIm in agreement with this change.  We asked for the removal of the question altogether we we wrote these ordersets and never got a satisfactory reason of why it is required.  The result level that triggers a call for a critical value is independent of whether the patient is on warfarin and Im not aware that the lab processes the speciment any differently based on the answer.  In any case, we probably need to understand why this question is being asked in the first place to address Phils comment.  Id personally prefer - On warfarin and No warfarin therapy since it would include everyone, but can live with the current options if it means not having to go back through HCG.\n\n\n\n\nRationale per Philip Lee\n\nthis is certainly ok for all order sets that I work on/am responsible for.\n\nthe term \"no anticoagulants\" may be misleading...what they really mean is \"not on warfarin\"....however, they could be on other anticoagulants like lovenox which does not affect the INR...and it is still appropriate to check that button.\n\ni think it is fine re: PT/INR orders.\n\nwe should not be ordering any aPTT labs anymore. it has been my intent to review order sets with aPTT to see if most (if not all) can be removed).\n\nin KPNC, we no longer use aPTT to follow heparin dosing...rather, anti-Xa assay for this. as a result, no baseline aPTT needs to be drawn either.\n\nthere is a rare time that we will check a baseline aPTT in evaluation for hypercoagulable state, but this is relatively uncommon and can be ordered ala carte when needed.',NULL,'1260307365ï££W508677ï££Status changed to WorkInProgress as Task CHG000004284081 has begun work.ï£¢',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-11 - Tina H Hamilton - PMO notes imported\nAs shown on HCG approved changes for Arrythmia ED orderset. Lorna Yamaguchi seeking ICU domain OK< but suggests that Phil Lee and Herb Szeto confirm needed build. See email sent 12/18/09 to Phil Lee and Herb Szeto. \n\n\n1/5/09 follow up note to all above, asking for rationale and approval in absence of any comments from Trevor, et al \n\n\n12/23/09 Phil Lee \nby the way, I actually prefer the \"INR\" label for the lab....on some order sets, it says \"PT\" and others \"PT/INR\"...we should standardize them all the same way on all the order sets. \n\n\nRemedy ticket created, note to build/orders team to ID impacted ordersets<BR><BR>2009-02-17 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, requires lab review. Plan, send to Ted Lynch for regional lab review.<BR><BR>2009-02-17 - Tina H Hamilton - Sent note with request to Fran Strychaz (cc Ted Lynch) for review by lab committee.<BR><BR>2009-02-18 - Tina H Hamilton - Fran Strychaz forwarded question to lab goverance (Thomas Lorey, David Levy, Robert X Greenberg<BR><BR>2009-02-19 - Tina H Hamilton - email from Dave Levy\nI looked closer and think I see why the lab may actually be the ones who requested anticoagulation status as a question.  It looks to me like it crosses the interface and gets picked up and presented with returned results.  Thus on the patient below I can see the result of the PT/INR and that the patient is anticoagulated on warfarin.  This is probably a good thing, so we dont have to search elsewhere for this important info. \n\nI recommend that we ask Herb to do what the ED has done and have orders that fill in the 2 most common options so the docs do not get stopped and have to - those would be PT/INR Baseline and PT/INR on Warfarin.\n\nSee my screenshot below to see what I am talking about on the results side.  Herb - can you agree with this?\n\n<BR><BR>2009-03-03 - Tina H Hamilton - aproved for swap on surgical order sets per Maggie Mentakis at TIGR meeting.<BR><BR>2009-03-12 - Tina H Hamilton - Inquiry sent to Fran Strychaz re: lab committee approval status<BR><BR>2009-03-20 - Tina H Hamilton - Herb Szeto inquiring re: status, He prefers;\nINR- Not taking warfarin (rather than currently on no anticoagulants)\nINR - On warfarin \nas the two options but to leave the two options as is if it required that we take back through HCG.\n\nFollow up email to Fran Strychaz and Dave Levy (cc Herb Szeto) re: status of lab committee approval and options for selection.<BR><BR>2009-03-26 - Tina H Hamilton - email from Herb Szeto to include HBS Atrial Fibrillation orderset as well.\n\nNote, per Tina HH, this change will require and extract to identify impacted ordersets and obtain domain approval to change or exclude from the change.<BR><BR>2009-03-26 - Tina H Hamilton - copied Fran Strychaz with above note, gentle reminder that we are still awaiting lab committee approval.<BR><BR>2009-03-27 - Tina H Hamilton - Recieved out of office response from Fran Strchaz, referring questions to Jeffrey M Hoffman moving forward, Note to Jeffrey Hoffman inquiring as to status.<BR><BR>2009-03-30 - Tina H Hamilton - email Jeffrey M Hoffman\nDue to recent changes in LWG leadership- -Dr. Levy passed the torch to Dr. Tom Lorey, Regional Lab Director- -we used our time in March to meet and determine a transition plan rather than hold the LWG as usual.  Therefore this issue has not yet been discussed.  We do, however, plan to reconvene the group in April and I will make sure that this is one of the topics on our agenda.\n<BR><BR>2009-03-31 - Tina H Hamilton - email agreement from Dave Levy, Tom Lorey and Herb Szeto to move forward.\nMap \"INR - No Warfarin Therapy\" to Baseline\nOptions for selection will be\n1) \"INR - No Warfarin therapy\" (mapped to Baseline)\n2) \"INR - On Warfarin\". (mapped to Warfarin)\n\nemail to Rob Norris, Lorna Yamaguchi, Maggie Mentakis, Elliiot Morrison and Jaya Mokkapati to change across domain ordersets.<BR><BR>2009-03-31 - Tina H Hamilton - Pending review by Mark Knoblauch, extract, and assignment to the appropriate build AC.<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - PeriOp domain approval to make change across Surgical (PeriOp and PostOP) ordersets.<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - email Dave Levy\nI think that the discussion is that ordersets should have INR on Warfarin and INR baseline in the same language and fashion as was done for the ED folks on their orderset.  Tom Lorey can give formal approval if that is what is needed by whatever process he feels is necessary here.  I think that if Herb and the ED Suite lead (cannot remember his name right now) agree, then probably worth doing this for all.  Tom Lorey the regional lab director is now leading the lab group and I am a part of his team, so I do not want to overstep here.\n\n\nI agree with Tom - baseline or none is probably best.  Maybe \"baseline\" is not so bad because it is fairly noncommital and would be closest to the idea of \"no warfarin\".  Probably covers 99% of the clinical scenarios that we care about.\n\n(For example:  Patients with DIC or severe liver disease with abnormal PT/INR would then have something that showed that their values were measured on no anticoagulation).<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - Note to Herb Szeto copying distribution list to confirm which lab orders are impacted; accompanied with screen shot of PT EAP record associated with varying display names (PT, PT/INR, etc). Are we now substituting PT with INR or only making this change when the display name is TP/INR or INR?<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - email Dave Levy\nI think that the key is that all single orders need to be replaced by 2 possibilities - PT/INR on warfarin and PT/INR on no warfarin therapy - as long as both of those choices replace a single choice on every order set, then I think we are ok and have made progress, allowing the clinician to answer the question by selecting proper choice instead of having to be stopped and answer the question\n\nApproved by Tom Lorey<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - secondary note per Phil Lee\nAlso, Phil asked if we could float the secondary request to the group, and that is, to review all ordersets and remove the aPTT and PTT orders as obtaining this baseline is no longer clinically useful (except in the case of hypercoagulapathy so on ordersets specific for that, leave the aPTT or PTT orders).\nIf this is agreed by the domains, we could do a consistent across the domain review of ordersets and update. \nThis may be considered a HIGH level change since it involves removing content that has been approved. We would need to circulate for review and comment and bring to the HCG after the domains agreed to this change.\n\nPhil Lee\nas a point of clarification, for KPNC, we NO LONGER use PTT to adjust heparin dosing. Rather, we use anti-Xa. \n\nAs a reflex (ie fall back to previous practices), physicians routinely check off PT/INR and PTT....in case heparin might be used later. there is no value in checking baseline PTT (or anti-Xa for that matter) prior to initiation of heparin. \n\nthis is the rationale for the suggestion.\n\n(This is a high level change that will require a separate SR. Tina HH to create)<BR><BR>2009-04-01 - Tina H Hamilton - Change to PT/INR orders approved by Elliot Morrison (via email)\nApproved by Maggie Mentakis, email\nApproved by Herb Szeto, email<BR><BR>2009-04-06 - Tina H Hamilton - email Rob Norris\nyes, so approved-- chief among them would be the STEMI and chest pain ordersets, GI Bleed, Alcohol with Complications; Im sure there are others.\n<BR><BR>2009-05-29 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Met with Britt Mattern about the extraction and discovered a streamlined approach to finding the list of order sets with aPTT/PTT.<BR><BR>2009-06-19 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Lists of Order sets by domain sent to domain leads to determine which order sets to change.  See master list of ordersets attachment.<BR><BR>2009-08-03 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - As of 8/3/09, the Periop, Perinatal, ED, Med Surg and IS domains have submitted their lists of which order sets to make the changes to.  Emailed Pediatric and Critical Care domains requesting reply by 8/14/09 or we will assume that they agree to the changes.\n\nNote that anti-Xa will be added to order set 414314 ED Immediate Action Orthopedic order set and 414290 Altered level of Consciousness ED.<BR><BR>2009-08-27 - Tina H Hamilton - Sent domain reminder to L Yamguchi that approval is pending for critical care order sets.<BR><BR>2009-12-08 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Status changed to WorkInProgress as Task CHG000004284081 has begun work.<BR><BR>2009-12-15 - Gail L Gordon Gaskins - Requests for final approval of changes sent to domain leaders of IS, ED, Periop, M/S and Crit Care with the final list of changes to be made. Responses due by 12/29/09.  Final change will be implemented on 1/26/10.<BR><BR>',984,984,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2817,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3512524,NULL,'OS Multiple: revise, remove aPTT/PTT',NULL,'SR',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-03 08:02:47','2009-04-01 15:58:29',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',959,NULL,313,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-28 09:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OS Multiple: revise, remove aPTT/PTT\n\nElimination of aPTT or PTT orders as a \"routine\" baseline measurement OR as a method to monitor efficacy of heparin:\nRequest is to review all ordersets and remove the aPTT and PTT orders as obtaining this baseline is no longer clinically useful (except in the case of clinical concern about hypercoagulable state....on ordersets specific for that, leave the aPTT or PTT orders, though should change to ONE standardized way of naming it: either aPTT or PTT).   In KPNC, we NO LONGER use PTT to adjust heparin dosing. Rather, we use anti-Xa. \n\nAs a reflex (ie fall back to previous practices), physicians routinely check off PT/INR and PTT for many patients (e.g. preop, on admission to hospital, etc)....in case heparin might be used later. There is no value in checking baseline PTT (or anti-Xa for that matter) prior to initiation of heparin. \n\n\nthis is the rationale for the suggestion.\nPhilip C. Lee, MD, FACC\nCardiologist, Kaiser Permanente Santa Clara\nClinical Associate Professor, Stanford University\n(408) 851-3312 Tie-line 8-401-3312',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2818,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3633256,NULL,'NEW Order Set - See attachment, build new SQ Insulin Pump order set',NULL,'SR',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Pla','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','M','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-22 12:06:57','2009-05-11 14:23:12',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',984,NULL,313,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-28 09:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NEW Order Set - See attachment, build new SQ Insulin Pump order set',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-05-11 - Minh X Nguyen - Notes from email:\n\n\n\nPamela Kershner/CA/KAIPERM\n05/08/2009 05:19 PM	\n\nRe: Fw: continuous SUBQ insulin pump\n\nNancy, \nThanks for your comments.  I havent had time until now to review and update the order set. \n\nMinh:  The insulin pump order set is based on the carb counting order set already in place with adjustments in order to use it in pump patients. Enclosed is an updated version of the insulin pump order set. The insulin pump order set has been approved by the Regional Endocrine group.   Please see my comments in green below.\n\nAs part of the insulin pump orders, I also wanted to include the contraiindications under the Notes section in the orders:\n\nNOTES\nNote:\n  Use this order set only for insulin treated patients who are using the insulin pump for insulin therapy\nCONTRAINDICATIONS TO PUMP THERAPY\n*Patient with altered state of consciousness\n*Critically ill patient (e.g. sepsis, trauma) requiring intensive care\n*Patient at risk for suicide\n*Patient refuses or otherwise unable to participate in own care\n*Family member, friend, or significant other refuses or is otherwise unable to \n      participate in care if patient is unable to participate in own care\n*Other circumstances identified by the physician\n\nPamela Kershner, M.D.\n\n\n\nNancy Ichiuji/CA/KAIPERM\n05/08/2009 08:15 AM	\nTo\nMinh Nguyen/CA/KAIPERM@Kaiperm\n\nRe: Fw: continuous SUBQ insulin pump\n	\nThe SFO Diabetes Management Group has been working on a P&P and an order set for continuous subcutaneous insulin infusion (CSII). Dr Pamela Kersher from WCR has been working on a REGIONAL order set. I have cc her as well.\n\nI have attached the drafts of our P&P and order set\n\nTo answer your questions:\n1.  Are you looking to start the patients on the pump in house?  \nNo -  only patients who are on insulin pumps at home will be continued on insulin pumps in the hospital  \nYes, but rarely (we purchased a pump for the hospital).  We have started a few patients on the pump but they have usually been patients who have been hospitalized for a long time with unpredictable blood sugars and this was the only way we could stabilize their sugars well enough to be able to discharge them.\n2.  Are the patients to use their own pump?  If so, do you have (not sure if needed) a policy around this?\nPatients will use their own pump and provide all necessary equipment (pump, batteries, tubing). Patient will sign an agreement with conditions for using the pump. See attached  P&P and agreement.\nAgreed.\n3.  Are the patients doing their own pump programming?\nPatients will determine their insulin dose based on the doctors orders ( __ units of insulin per gram of carbs). Doctor will include the basal rate and correction dose in the order set.\nThe pump is usually programmed to their outpatient settings.  Any changes in basal as well as correction doses or carb ratios will have to be ordered by the MD and then either the diabetes RN (if available) or the patient can make the dose changes in the pump.\n\nWe currently do not have a consistent practice for use of the insulin pump. When patients are admitted with an insulin pump, they were usually switched to an insulin sliding scale. However, we recognize that maintaining the patient on the insulin pump while in the hospital may be beneficial; therefore, we need to develop guidelines for use of CSII. Your help in developing an order set will be greatly appreciated!\n\n<BR><BR>2009-05-11 - WSSTARTEAM - This SR is not configured to sync with StarTeam. For more details email askALM@kp.org<BR><BR>2009-05-12 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, Tina HH to send to HCG co-leads for guidance on need for regional P&Pto support patient use of equipment while hospitalized.<BR><BR>2009-05-19 - Tina H Hamilton - Paul Feigenbaum defers decision on regional policy to Anita Zuniga. Anita Zuniga has referred to Barbara Norrish for recommendations; pending response from Barbara Norrish.<BR><BR>2009-05-22 - Tina H Hamilton - Anita Zuniga consulting with Barbara Norrish.<BR><BR>2009-05-22 - Tina H Hamilton - Follow up note to Herb Szeto and Pam Kershner inquiring re: status of regional order set build, protocols.<BR><BR>2009-05-22 - Tina H Hamilton - For review at 5/26/09 Med Surg domain mtg; Barbara Norrish and Doug OBrien to participate.<BR><BR>2009-06-27 - Tina H Hamilton - RASD Minutes, circulated by Rohanna Heredia:\nIt was suggested that we will need a Regional Policy for the Insulin Pumps. This issue will go to the Regional Nursing Pharmacy meeting to start writing the policy. Then the policy will go to the Regional Domains for approval.<BR><BR>2009-08-10 - Tina H Hamilton - Inquiry to Herb Szeto and Anne Foss-Durant; has the pharmacy nursing group developed the policy, is there a target date?<BR><BR>2009-08-12 - Tina H Hamilton - Per Herb Szeto, Doug OBrien and Barbara Norrish are working offline to develop a policy. Inquiry sent to Doug and Barbara to see if they can provide an update at the next med surg meeting.<BR><BR>2009-08-13 - Tina H Hamilton - email from Doug OBrien to Herb Szeto outlining status. He is working with Molly Clopp.\nWe discussed the proposed policy at the Inpatient Pharmacy Directors Meeting, and we gathered the concerns of the IPDs.\n2.  We had an initial discussion at the June 9th meeting of the NoCal Nursing-Pharmacy Committee meeting.  The nurses had some concerns and also wanted to collect feedback from some of the front-line staff.\n3.  The follow-up discussion was to take place on Tuesday (8/11) at the NoCal Nursing-Pharmacy Committee, but the meeting had to be delayed.  Feedback on the order set was also obtained from Dr. Sue Stevens (Endocrinologist, Vallejo).\n4.  We are rescheduling the NoCal Nursing-Pharmacy Committee meeting to August 31, and we will have more feedback and recommendations for the Domain at the conclusion of this meeting.\n<BR><BR>2009-09-23 - Tina H Hamilton - Confirmed with Herb Szeto, no further updates from Doug OBrien or Molly Clopp. Domain will bring this forward once they have been provided the policy.<BR><BR>',981,981,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2819,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3576522,NULL,'OS Revision CRRT Heparin SRO KPHC IP ADULT',NULL,'SR',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'