hat was originally submitted.  For instance, the SR that you sent me screens everyone over the age of 60 OR BMI<18 whereas the original criteria was everyone with BMI<18.5.  Im concerned that we will be ordering alot more albulmins that we need to with the revised criteria.  In any case, it should be OK as long as we are able to discuss with the AC at the time of the build to fine tune.\n\nCHG000003425624\nCHG000003425701\n\n1)  Using PRL functionality have a lab order for albumin and Pre-albumin show up defaulted in the HBS admission and rounding ordersets if ONE of the following criteria are met:   (Patients who have had those labs done in the last month should be excluded.)\na patients BMI is <18.5.  OR\na patient has had greater than a 10% drop in weight defined as (Highest recorded weight in the last year - current weight)/current weight > 10%\n\nAs a prerequisite to the above request, those labs would need to be added to those ordersets with NEXT AM as the frequency\nIf this is not possible then build a BPA that would alert the MD to order those labs when the criteria are met.  The BPA should be embedded into the admission and rounding navigators.\n\n\n2)  Create a BPA that would direct the MD to enter Protein Calorie Malnutrition in the Problem List. if  BOTH of the following criteria were met: (Must have one from #1 and # from #2)\n1.	Albumin <3 OR Pre-Albumin <12\n2.	BMI<18.5 OR patient has had greater than a 10% drop in weight\n\nCurrent proposed language that the nutritionists are to use in the \"Dear Doctor\" note.  We dont have final agreement on the text but it will be similar.\nConsider adding Protein Calorie Malnutrition *** (Code ***) to the problem list and also address it in your note – Protein Calorie Malnutrition Moderate/Severe (select the appropriate diagnosis): followed by RD. See RD note for details.\n\n<BR><BR>2009-04-07 - Christie F Vidal - Changed SR to WIP and Crteated the below BPAs  in WITS 2 Lead:\n\nSG CR HBS AMIT/ROUNDING ALBUMIN IP NCAL #3674\n\nSG RL HBS AMIT/ROUNDING ALBUMIN IP NCAL #3673<BR><BR>2009-04-14 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review and comparison of both SRs, analysis; contents of \"duplicate\" requests and Dr. Szetos original emails shared with build team for clarification. Build team requesting content and scope confirmation, and agreement to close one SR to allow request management. Phone message left for Herb Szeto to call Tina HH. \n<BR><BR>2009-04-15 - Tina H Hamilton - Confirmation from Herb Szeto\nSR #CHG000003425624\n Confirm impacted order sets; HBS Admission and HBS Rounding Long, HBS Rounding Short\nAdd Albumin and Pre-Albumin, NEXT AM\nAdd locator logic as listed in #1\n1)  Using PRL functionality have a lab order for albumin and Pre-albumin show up defaulted in the HBS admission and rounding ordersets if ONE of the following criteria are met:   (Patients who have had those labs done in the last month should be excluded.)\na patients BMI is <18.5.  OR\na patient has had greater than a 10% drop in weight defined as (Highest recorded weight in the last year - current weight)/current weight > 10%\n\nEXCLUSION CRITERIA:  Active orders for albulmin and pre-albulmin are already in the system or those labs have resulted in the last 30 days.\n\nNote: duplicate SR 3425701 is being closed for same request.\nOther SR 3435460 is still active, for BPA\n\nconfirmed\nThe build team is continuing to work with Epic and SCAL to see what can be built. Sherry and I spoke and she is thinking that the most likely ETA would be the 7/22/09 release, assuming your approval of the build by 5/12.\n<BR><BR>2009-05-04 - Tina H Hamilton - email confirmation from Herb Szeto that locator logic for SCAL BPA with similar requirements exists. Forwarded email information to Chris Vidal and Sherry Ellis.\n<BR><BR>2009-06-24 - Christie F Vidal - After three meetings with Stephanie G. We were unsuccessful of creating a working BPA. We are contacting Epic. \nStephaine was told to place project on hold per Brian.<BR><BR>2009-07-28 - Christie F Vidal - Sent below e-mail to Stephanie:\n\nHello Stephaine,\n\nThe SR # CHG000003425624 we worked on a few months ago regarding a BPA was put on hold I believe you told me per Brian. I wanted to see if this was something that we could begin working on again or is this something that is still on hold. Please let me know when you think we could pick this project back up. \nThank you in advance, \n<BR><BR>2009-09-17 - Christie F Vidal - Met with Stephanie to discuss BPA, reviewed that the previous build that was in WITS 2 was not pulling the information from the flowsheet correctly. Unable to work on this today since WITS 3 in down scheduling time next week to review.<BR><BR>2009-10-30 - Christie F Vidal - E-mailed Stephainie to schedule time to work on this BPA.<BR><BR>',1093,974,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2830,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3440557,NULL,'OS HBS: Stroke Ordersets:  Title Changes, synonyms, related ICD-9 codes',NULL,'SR',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-27 10:08:14','2009-10-28 17:02:36','2009-11-02 11:42:13','2009-03-10 08:36:12',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',965,NULL,313,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-28 09:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OS HBS: Stroke Ordersets, Title Changes, synonyms: see email attachment 3/10/09\n\ninclude the word \"Inpatient\" in the title of the ISCHEMIC STROKE HBS IP NCAL and  INTRACEREBRAL HEMORRHAGE HBS IP NCAL ordersets.  \n(Note, request to replace \"Admission\" with \"Inpatient\" per Herb Szeto and Rob Norris 4/13/09)\n\nRename VCA/TIA Initial Eval to CVA/TIA ED AND INITIAL EVAL\n\n\nAdd CVA as \"CVA\" is added as a synonym to each of these ordersets:\nSTROKE SYMPTOMS EMERGENCY STANDARDIZED PROCEDURE\nCVA/TIA INITIAL EVAL \nTHROMBOLYTICS FOR STROKE orderset \nISCHEMIC STROKE HBS IP NCAL admission orderset \nINTRACRANIAL HEMORRHAGE ED NCAL\nINTRACEREBRAL HEMORRHAGE HBS IP NCAL admission orderset\n\n\nAdd \"TIA\" as a synonym to the  ISCHEMIC STROKE HBS IP NCAL \n\nRefer to attachment for ICD9 codes to associate with each orderset\n\n3/11/09\nLooks like getting the suggested work flow sent out to everyone would be a good idea (maybe a particular message to HBS and ED chiefs). Furthermore a what;s new and web link would be great\nPer David Levy;\nuse web links inside the orderset itself to help clarify.\n\nFor example we could have text at the top that says something like:\n\"This orderset is designed to be used by ED physicians and Nurses for evaluating suspected stroke.  There are several other ordersets for evaluating and treating stroke patients - for a complete discussion of what they are and when to use each, please click this link\"  (and then clicking the link launches web page with the info below on what each order set is and who and when to use it).\n\nSee attachment with workflow from Rob Norris',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2831,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3512365,NULL,'KPHC - INP2: OS Rev Multiple; removal of CK-MB (see comments)',NULL,'SR',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Res','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-09-16 13:54:18','2009-10-27 13:55:18','2009-10-27 10:15:58','2009-11-02 11:42:15','2009-04-01 15:34:20',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1018,NULL,313,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-28 09:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OS Rev Multiple; removal of CK-MB and aPTT/PTT\n\nSelective replacement of CK and CK-MB orders with troponin order:\nWe were asked by Regional Lab to review the order sets to develop consistency with KPNC ACS Guideline regarding cardiac markers used to assess for myocardial injury and myocyte necrosis (i.e. myocardial infarction). Historically, CK and CK-MB have been the markers used. In 2007, the Joint European Society of Cardiology-ACC-AHA-World Health Federation Task Force established troponin as the biomarker of choice for this purpose. The KPNC Acute Coronary Syndrome Team has also adopted this perspective.\n\nAs such, in general, the order sets should be reviewed to see where it is appropriate to replace the orders for CK and CK-MB, with troponin. This is especially relevant for post-surgical patients where there is a greater likelihood that elevations in CK and CK-MB are the result of skeletal muscle injury rather than myocardial injury. For some cardiac patients, it is reasonable to leave the option of ordering CK and CK-MB since this may supplement \"sizing\" of an MI (when used in conjunction with troponin I measurement).\n\nElimination of aPTT or PTT orders as a \"routine\" baseline measurement OR as a method to monitor efficacy of heparin:\nRequest is to review all ordersets and remove the aPTT and PTT orders as obtaining this baseline is no longer clinically useful (except in the case of clinical concern about hypercoagulable state....on ordersets specific for that, leave the aPTT or PTT orders, though should change to ONE standardized way of naming it: either aPTT or PTT).   In KPNC, we NO LONGER use PTT to adjust heparin dosing. Rather, we use anti-Xa. \n\nAs a reflex (ie fall back to previous practices), physicians routinely check off PT/INR and PTT for many patients (e.g. preop, on admission to hospital, etc)....in case heparin might be used later. There is no value in checking baseline PTT (or anti-Xa for that matter) prior to initiation of heparin.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2832,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3521927,NULL,'addition of a \"DELAY IN ANTIBIOTICS\" order to the Pneumonia ED orderset and Pneumonia HBS orderset',NULL,'SR',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Clo','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N','A',NULL,'NR',' ','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-22 11:06:02','2009-08-28 12:16:43','2009-10-28 09:08:42','2009-04-05 09:46:27',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1018,NULL,313,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00