e (see attachement dated today).  If additional respiratory micro labs are desired, Janet (or site support) to update this SR with requested labs.  THH will then forward request to domain leads (HBS, ED , ICU) and direct questions to Janet and Dr. Franco.<BR><BR>2009-12-02 - Tina H Hamilton - Screen shots and list of labs sent to domain leads for a final approval of labs per each order set. Also, noted Remedy note requesting different hypersal for pedi CF patients so need to circle back to pharmacy to verify that the build as shown is OK for pedi CF.\nPlan, if Adult domains approve build and labs on all listed order sets, send for review and comment this month, for HCG 1/20/10.<BR><BR>2009-12-02 - Tina H Hamilton - email Christina Shih; I think I said I thought the EDs would rarely use this but it was okay to add.  Could it be collapsed?didng the labs are okay, we would use the AFB and fungal, for instance.  Cytologies rarely. \nJami DeSantiago: This looks like a good idea to me, I can support this change to the order sets.\nHerb Szeto: Yes, as long as the section is collapsed.<BR><BR>2009-12-02 - Tina H Hamilton - Lorna Yamaguchi: agree. Also collapsed is a good idea.<BR><BR>2009-12-02 - Tina H Hamilton - email to Emily Foo and Dan Brugger inquiring as to status of build and approval per Albin Leongs dosing recommendations.<BR><BR>2009-12-02 - Tina H Hamilton - Med Surg, Jami DeSantiago: This looks like a good idea to me, I can support this change to the order sets.\nChristina Shih: approved, collapsed<BR><BR>2009-12-08 - Sherry Ellis - Demonstrated build in Pulmonary Suit meeting today.  Received feedback and resent updated screen shots (cced Barbara Sheldon and Janet Margolis, see attachment)  requesting feedback or approval of build.<BR><BR>2009-12-08 - Sherry Ellis - Dr. Gupta suggested in addition to a \"stand alone\" orderset, we add this to the HBS pneumonia order set only<BR><BR>',1003,1003,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2842,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',3201970,NUL