ion has introduced several new performance measures around Venous Thromboembolism.  \nVTE-3 requires 5 or more days of overlap therapy with warfarin and injectable anticoagulant for patients with VTE AND INR >=2 prior to discontinuation of the injectable anticoagulant.\nVTE-4 requires patients receiving IV unfractionated heparin have dosage/platelet monitoring by defined parameters such as a nomogram or protocol.\n\nPhysician Sponsor Name:\nHerb Szeto, MD, MPH,\nCo-Chair, NCAL KPHC Med Surg Domain\n\nMalti Charlu\nRegional Anticoagulation Physician Champion\n\n\nDomain/SUIT that has approved the content:\n<Regional Med Surg Domain>',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-11-03 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review; HIGH level changes of decision support that affect physician selection and ordering of anticoagulation medications. Priority, Fast Track level change due to changes in JC.<BR><BR>2009-11-04 - Tina H Hamilton - Background/context received from Herb Szeto, added to description<BR><BR>2009-12-16 - Minh X Nguyen - sent screenshots to Dr. Szeto.<BR><BR>',1406,974,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2858,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Maggie Mentakis','Gabrielle Levine',4196088,NULL,'SSC: Medication adds to Postop HAS ASC Orders IP NCAL [414410] Order Set',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','R','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Pen','SUR','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','Resource Assignment','M','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','PERI','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-22 12:07:11','2009-10-29 10:23:53',' ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',967,NULL,95,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-03 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',