L,NULL,NULL,NULL,'(SR) MCH - Perinatal - OS:  Preterm Steroid Medication. \nOne of the Perinatal core measures reporting is - Antenatal steroids for preterm labors - 24 to 32 weeks. They need to report \"Reason steroids not given\" if steroids were not administered before delivery.\nCurrently we do not document in a discrete field. Some providers do document in their notes.  It would be helpful for a lot of initiatives. See attachement for more details.\nRequest as follows: \n1.	Create an order - \"Reason steroids not ordered\" with a smart list in it.  \na.	Available in our preference list.\nb.	Add to \"Preterm Labor order set\". \ni.	Not a hard stop with required order.\nii.	Just an additional order in the order set under the corticosteroid medications section.\n2.	Have a BPA (best practice alert) for providers in the MD Labor navigator and MD Antepartum Rounding navigator.\n3.             Criteria for BPA \n> BPA for all pts admitted between 24 and 34\n> Steroids were not given in the last 12 weeks (either inpatient or outpatient). \n> Suppress BPA if a \"Reason steroids not ordered\" was ordered.\n> Have a choice to open \"Preterm labor order set\" \n> Should trigger only if Steroids are not ordered and Resaon for steroids is not ordered.\n> Should have \"Reason steroids not given\" order prechecked in the alert, where they can accept the order and sign.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-11-09 - Tina H Hamilton - Initial review of SR, seems to be missing attachment, details or indication of domain approval. Note to Ann Wolff and Robbie Zampa, asking for updates. Set to [pending requestor information] status, owner Robbie Zampa pending updates.<BR><BR>2009-11-09 - Robbie Zampa - Approved 10/27. Attached Detail and Approval document.  Updated Description.<BR><BR>2009-11-10 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review. Order set change is a medium level change. Assigned to Jennifer Koster, pending resource assignment.\nThe BPA is a separate request that needs another SR. Gail Gaskins is