lar uterine contractions and cervix is 3 cm dilated.\n\nAmpicillin 2 Gram IV (Loading Dose): Change ordering fequency from one time to see instruction. \nInstructions: Attach vial to 100 ml 0.9% sodium chloride IV bag using vial adaptor system.   Activate and dilute before administration.  Administer: (1) when or if bag of water is ruptured, or (2) if patient has regular uterine contractions and cervix is 3 cm dilated.\n\nCefazolin (ancef/kefzol) 2 gram IV (Loading Dose): Change ordering fequency from one time to see instruction. \nInstruction: Attach vial to 100 ml 0.9% sodium chloride IV bag using vial adaptor system.   Activate and dilute before administration.  Administer: (1) when or if bag of water is ruptured, or (2) if patient has regular uterine contractions and cervix is 3 cm dilated.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-11-30 - Robbie Zampa - Approved by NCAL Regional Perinatal Domain.<BR><BR>2009-12-01 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, this is a medium level change that does not change the order intent. This directs the nurses to see the admin instructions and avoids having the order drop off MAR. Requires that the admin instructions be provided by the domain, in lieu of timed \"start time\". Plan for 1/26 release pending domain confirmation of admin instructions.<BR><BR>2009-12-07 - Thomas Chun - Emailed Domain sponsors seeking clarification on start time and open discussion on impact frequency change.<BR><BR>2009-12-07 - Thomas Chun - reply from EM:\n\nTom,\nJaya can give you a full explanation, but the intent of this change is to minimize the risk that loading dose will not be given.\nCurrent state: In those facilities that delay first dose until \"active labor\", the order drops entirely off the MAR if the nurses mark \"not given\" when it overdue.\nWith suggested change: In same facilities, the loading dose will not show up as overdue, but the maintenance dose will continue to show up overdue. After discussion with nursing, this is felt to be a sufficient reminder to the nurses to give the loading dose. I.e., if they see the maintenance dose come up as due, they will not give it without checking that the loading dose was previously given. Worst case scenario, they get two maintenance doses, and should be close to same serum levels.\n\nElliot Morrison, MD\nOb/Gyn Santa Rosa\n707-393-4864\n8-533-4864<BR><BR>2009-12-17 - Robbie Zampa - Updated Descriptioin with Instructions as requested.<BR><BR>',1294,935,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2894,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',4278389,NULL,'Day of surgery HAS ASC ORDERS orderset - Measure vital signs is showing \"PACU\" and it should be \"Preop\".',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Pla','GYN','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','PERI','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-22 12:07:28','2009-11-24 11:01:50',' ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',984,NULL,201,201,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-30 12:45:00','2009-12-03 09:09:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Day of surgery HAS ASC ORDERS orderset - Measure vital signs is showing \"PACU\" and it should be \"Preop\".\n\nThe request is to change the verbiage in ord