uild requirements sent to her through e-mail',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-12-22 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review, per Emily Foo, to follow up on build documents receipt. Placed in planning status, Emily to follow up with Dan Brugger to 1) confirm that this has been approved by the regional PICU domain and 2) obtain build documents.<BR><BR>',994,994,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2924,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',4021695,NULL,'OS ED Pneumonia, add smart group for Antibiotic delay',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Pen','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Enhancement','Resource Assignment','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,'2009-11-07 00:00:00','2009-11-07 12:01:00',NULL,'2009-12-22 12:07:39','2009-09-04 14:40:36',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1018,NULL,95,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-17 11:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Update 12/15/09: Since we can not have a BPA fire when the physician is signing the pneumonia order set, the ED domain has decided to put smart group in the Pneumonia ED order set. The new smart group will contain the order DELAY IN ANTIBIOTIC THERAPY (EAP 218416). The order should be defualted. A new restriction locator should be attached to the smart group so that the smart group displays only if the patient has been in the ED for more than 5 hours 30 minutes. This can be done by creating a rule (CER). -Michelle Donnelly',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2009-09-04 - Stanley E Deutsch - Initial Approval:  Stan Deutsch<BR><BR>2009-09-04 - Stanley E Deutsch - Needs further analysis and clarification of exactly how this BPA should work.<BR><BR>2009-10-30 - Michelle C Donnelly - Figured out how to build MD BPA to the requirements. Emailed Rob and Steve to confirm the details.<BR><BR>2009-12-15 - Michelle C Donnelly - Forwarding SR to the order set team.\n\nSince we can not have a BPA fire when the physician is signing the pneumonia order set, the ED domain has decided to put smart group in the Pneumonia ED order set. The new smart group will contain the order DELAY IN ANTIBIOTIC THERAPY (EAP 218416). The order should be defualted. A new restriction locator should be attached to the smart group so that the smart group displays only if the patient has been in the ED for more than 5 hours 30 minutes. This can be done by creating a rule (CER).<BR><BR>2009-12-15 - Sherry Ellis - See Michelle for build requirements.<BR><BR>2009-12-22 - Tina H Hamilton - TIGR review. Confirmed with Michelle Donnelly that the original request for a BPA has been converted to a smart group. (THis is the original request; BPA Antibiotics\n\nAntibiotics BPA\nThe BPA logic would be as follows:\n\nMD:  a BPA would fire if an MD signs an order for an antibiotic from the Pneumonia ED orderset if the patient has been in the ED 5 hrs 45 minutes or longer.  The alert should only fire for antibiotic medications ordered from this orderset, not any antibiotic.  When the alert fires, it should say:  \"\"Based on the length of time this patient has been in the ED, there is a potential for delay in antibiotic administration past 6 hours.  Would you like to document the Reason for Delay?\"\"  The alert would have the delay order in the window as an option for the MD to select, similar to how the lactate order appears if we order a blood culture w/o the lactate.\n\nRN:  there are two alerts Im thinking of-- one would fire when the RN acknowledges an antibiotic order in the PER if a patient has been in the ED > 6 hours-- alert would ask RN to remind/inform MD that the antibiotic is being given outside of the 6-hour window.  (Alternately, I wonder if such a BPA, if possible, could also allow the RN to document reason for delay via the order popping up for them, but its probably for the MD to actually document that).  The other BPA would fire when the RN acknowledges an antibiotic order if there is no blood culture done or ordered on the patient-- the BPA would remind them to do blood cultures first, and to make sure the correct culture and med admin times are documented.  Ideally these alerts would only fire for antibiotic orders that are from the Pneumonia ED orderset-- they should not fire for every antibiotic order.  Dont know if this is possible or not.\nOf these alerts, the MD alert would be the most useful.  The RN alert(s) would be nice, though I have some reservations about alerts like this which an end-user could \"\"blow past\"\" if they fire too much.\")\n\nTIGR discussion, regarding proposed build, requires confirmation of requirements from Rob Norris.  EAP is already in order set.\nAssigned to Chris Vidal, pending resource assignment. \n\n\n<BR><BR>',1423,983,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2925,0,'N',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Michael Horberg','',4337440,NULL,'OS New Needle Stick Order Sets for Blood and Body Fluid Exposure',NULL,'OS',NULL,'Stage',NULL,'0','L','N','H','S','needle stick',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NICE','Pla','0','KPHC CN IP ORDERSETS',NULL,'End User Applications','KPHC Inpatient MD/CRNA/Midwife Content','Order Set - MD','','L','N','N',' ',NULL,'NR',' ','N','ED','0','0','0','0','0','0','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-22 12:07:40','2009-12-15 13:44:17',' ','',NULL,NULL,N